improve population quality require transfer reproduction right to the rich ?
through free exchange on the market , nearly everything can be buy and sell .
today , the right to bear a second child be also become a popular product with the rich .
they have money to buy the right , to bear the child , and to raise the child .
as to these transfer and transaction of the right to bear a second child , let 's have a look at how the representative argue and legally struggle with government official at the " two meeting ".
why do they propose such a transfer on the right to bear a second child ?
to this question , li xinghao @-@ the author of this proposal , npc representative and chairman of zhigao group , say that such a transfer be beneficial to improve the quality of the population .
transfer to which kind of person , exactly ?
this representative identify 3 group : first , people with strong educational background ; second , the rich class ; third , civil servant .
li xinghao assert that " in today 's society , people with strong educational background , the rich class , and civil servant have relatively high social status , relatively good economics mean , and can ensure basic educational condition and a good environment for the newborn population to develop in ".
why be such transfer practical ?
li xinghao give his own specific explanation from the angle of market supply and demand .
he say , " for a transfer , people be not classify into the rich and the poor , but into those who have a demand and those who do not .
he say that the original motive for this proposal be root in his discovery that some family legally allow to bear a second child , due to their poverty and other reason , would become even more impoverished if they be to do so ;
while some rich family have a strong desire to bear a second child but do not have the allowance to do so .
he think that this conflict really exist , and the relevant governmental department can take the initiative to establish a transfer platform ."
this transfer proposal by representative li be indeed very smart .
on the one hand , it help the government to reduce and narrow the gap of wealth ;
on the other hand , it also solve the structural conflict of the reproduction right market @-@ the poor have allowance but cannot afford the birth and upbringing , while the rich want to bear children but do n't have the allowance .
based on representative li 's proposal , the rich will voluntarily reduce their per capita wealth by bear and raise more children , while the poor will increase their per capita wealth by bear and raise fewer children .
through such transfer and transaction of the right to bear a second child between the rich and the poor , the government can unnoticeably narrow the ever @-@ increase gap between the poor and the rich without spend a single cent .
how can the wealth gap be narrow through such transfer ?
this representative li have envision a fast track for the get @-@ rich @-@ first people to guide and assist the get @-@ rich @-@ later people . that be , " the allowance transferee shall give the transferor ' an entire sequence ' of help and support ."
" accord to li xinghao 's plan , through lottery @-@ type draw , the transfer platform establish a one @-@ on @-@ one guidance and assistance relationship between the transferee and the transferor .
as part of the assistance , the couple apply for the allowance to be transfer in to them will buy the transfer couple all the basic insurance currently require by the government , include social insurance , medical insurance , and personal accident insurance , and will continue to provide them with a minimum live guarantee for the rest of their life .
meanwhile , the applicant couple will also provide financial support for the education of the transfer couple 's child until he or she graduate from university .
what 's more , if the transfer couple intend to register as permanent urban resident , the applicant couple shall buy them a 35m2 socially subsidize apartment in the city where the applicant dwell , but all of the transfer couple 's land use right in the countryside will belong to the applicant couple ."
what do our family plan official think of this proposal that the state " utilize the transfer of right to bear a second @-@ child to improve the population quality and make the get @-@ rich @-@ first help the get @-@ rich @-@ later so as to realize common prosperity "?
in response , " yesterday , zhang feng , director of guangdong provincial family plan commission , make his stance clear to the media that the right to reproduce be absolutely not transferrable .
in the event that the right to reproduce be transfer , it would not only be a violation of law , but also bring moral question if it involve a transaction ."
through transfer their right to bear a second child and the concomitant obligation impose on the transferees , the poor can get rich with the guidance and assistance from the get @-@ rich @-@ first class , if the proposal can pass and become law , the poor undoubtedly have find in the rich class , well @-@ educate class , and the bureaucratic class an obedient son to provide for them up until they die . marvelous indeed .
he claim it be not a transaction , but how can it be otherwise ? in this bundle of obligation for common prosperity , where be the dignity of the poor ?
do not the bundle of obligation propose by this representative li still imply a contract on the exchange and transaction of land use right ?
certainly , without such exchange of interest , why would the rich take an interest in provide for the children of the poor ?
if the legislature really want to adopt this proposal on the premise of the get @-@ rich @-@ first class lead the get @-@ rich @-@ later class to become rich by give them one @-@ on @-@ one guidance and assistance so as to improve our population quality and narrow our wealth gap , it must ensure fairness in such exchange of interest and during the transfer .
transfer together with a wet nurse .
follow it with interest .
for a transfer of the right to marry , people be not classify into the rich and the poor , but into those who have a demand and those who do not . since i discover that some men who have a legal right to marry , due to their poverty and other reason , would become even more impoverished if they do marry ;
while some rich men have a strong desire to marry n concubine ( because their mistress often fuss about want to get marry ) but they do not have the allowance , and would be guilty of bigamy .
i think that this conflict really exist , and the relevant governmental department can take the initiative to establish a platform to transfer the right to marry .
