accord to most analyse , from within and without the petroleum industry , the world supply of oil , relative consumption , will effectively peak in the next decade .
what do this mean ?
if demand exceed supply , someone will neccessarily have to go without .
the issue be who ?
some nation will be price out , most likely the relatively undeveloped country in which automotive transportation be not really essential .
however , when there be not enough oil to satisfy even the industrialized nation , which totally depend on oil not only for transportation , but for farm , various chemical industry , etc. , how will they likely respond ?
obviously , war be a possiblity ; they have be fight for far less in the past .
of course , access to petroleum itelf be not the only issue .
most of the world 's food be grow use modern farm method that require enormous amount of gas .
if the amount of surplus food suddenly decrease as a result of peak oil , the poor around the world will starve , lamentable in itself , cause instability that could lead to conflict over scarce resoures .
china come to mind .
the economy of that nation be be build , with questionable logic by the central planner , on the western model : i.e. dependent on cheap petroleum .
what be unique about china be that the rule party 's legitmacy be intimately assosciated with rapid economic progress .
if this be suddenly to halt or risk collapse , would that rule party push the country into war , either to acquire access to oil or simply as a distraction , as so many authoritarian regime have do in the past ?
there be shift of power occuring in asia , as china and russia exert their influence .
the shangai cooperation organization of which they , along with ian , pakistan and most of the former soviet republic , be memebers , have state that it intend to remove u.s. influence from the region and failitate the rise of a ' multi @-@ polar world .'
i do n't want to guess their specific motive , but it seem to me that such an arrangement could be very advanategous for those nation in the event of a crisis bring on by peak oil .
between russia and iran , they would have access to enormous oil reserve , from which they could , if supply be too short , deny the u.s. saudi arabia come to mind as well .
as anyone who have do even the most superficial research on that nation would know , the house of saud be a joke , a paper tiger and a tyranny hate by most of its people .
if election be hold their , or if there be a struggle for power , the regime that woudl arise would be friendly with iran and extremely antagonistic to the u.s.: quite understandably i might add .
with the largest oil reserve in the world , it be vital that the u.s. maintain contorl over saudi arabia , which mean prop up the house of saud , and it would be equally benificial to iran or to china and its partner in asia to facilitate a revolution there , which would allow them greater access by default .
and so , after all that , which you might justly consider paranoia , my question be basically this ; in light of the threat of peak oil , and of the general decline in american economic might relative the rest of the world ( not to mention the current u.s. crisis ) , what do think the world will look like in a decade or two ?
if american hegemony fail , as appear inevitable , what will be its replacement ?
