even if it set transportation , technology and civilization in general back some , i 'd think a " reboot in a better direction " ( read : away from finite resource , fossil fuel ) be so much the better .
yea , more war over oil resource be likely ; perhaps even inevitable .
there be no question that the come century will see a confluence and will be a critical turn point in human history .
peak oil will be one of the primary driver of this process .
we may very well be call upon to choose between collective life and death .
the potential be there for both .
if we so choose to do so the technology we will have available in the near term future be perfectly capable of salvage the situation .
but if we do n't and we allow our technological civilisation to collapse under its own weight , the next generation of human will have to do without the major step stone of an oil based economy .
there simply will not be enough oil leave .
they may not be able to kickstart their own industrial era .
i think what you be go to see be a shift towards localize economy .
as the oil supply become smaller and population grow there just will not be enough to fee the system .
hopefully , people realize that it be go to take oil to move beyond oil , so the focus should be use what be readily available wisely , before the shift become extremely expensive .
