i could n't for the life of me figure out where to post this question , so i think i 'd put it here since it 's biologically relevant... somewhat .
do n't ask me why but i need to know what happen if you dye your eyebrow .
say you want to disguise yourself by bleach dark hair blonde and that you want to do the eyebrow as well to complete the disguise .
now the hair on your head will eventually grow and you 'll lose the blonde @-@ ness , but what about the eyebrow ?
i do n't remember ever have them cut or trim , so would they stay blonde ?
eyebrow have a different " terminal length " than head @-@ hair -- that be , they grow to a certain length ( and not longer ) , then fall out .
they 're still go through the growth process , though .
the old one fall out , the new one fall in .
so it 'd have to be re @-@ done at interval , yep .
this excessive concern with little eyebrow be a trifle odd .
i do n't think soz be look to disguise herself .
i think she 's on the vamp .
accord to darwin it be the male who do the vamp .
what 's the scientific explanation of the reversal in human ?
its the same with long @-@ haired dog and short @-@ haired dog .
the short haired dog have hair strand that ( on the average ) fall out or break before the average long @-@ haired dog 's .
eyebrow hair grow much slower than head hair , so if you dye everything together , your head hair will show " root " long before the eyebrow do .
i dye my eyebrow all the time , whether i 'm do a touch up to the root , or my entire head .
so , that 's every 2 week .
i do n't know how fast my eyebrow grow , but after 2 week there 's always a grey one in there somewhere .
i guess they grow as fast as women seem to need to pluck them .
btw , when you 're die them , use a q @-@ tip , and make sure you get it all the way to the root .
