a " theory " be nothing more than an explanation of know facts...when and if the fact change , the theory would be expect to change . therefore , any propose " theory " that be not support by know fact be to be reject . however , support for any one theory do not
automatically lead to a rejection of a second or even a third if those
theory be also support by the fact .
fact , not interpetations , be the basis for evaluation . an open and
curious mind and a regard for truth be still the basis for good science .
media coverage and political support be not .
it 's a common argument that the universe be tune " just so " for life to exist , and that any slight modification mean that " life " would be impossible .
but this premise assume that life as we know it be the only form of life that *can* exist . and i disagree with this assumption .
the life we see around us evolve in this universe as condition allow , so it 's not surprising at all that everything fit nicely . other universe with different rule would necessarily have life in them which fit that universe . and universe which be sterile have no life in them to question the fact that they be not there .
the really interesting thing to realize be that life evolve in universe ( at least this one ) at all . be the evolution of life in a universe pure chance , or be it inevitable ?
in our universe at least , life not only can exist , but do exist . and that mean that our universe be itself , alive , in a very real sense . and we be its thought .
a variant on the multi universe which seem to me obvious , and very real , be the infinite universe .
here the universe that we perceive be simply one cell of infinity , the others be like or unlike " cell " beyond our own , but fill the remainder of " everything " beyond our specific " this " with " otherthings ", identical , or not .
if we look at the magnitudinal stratification of this universe we go from , as we interpret it , and with our current ability to decern at sub nano level , the smallest subatomic particle through atom , molecule , solid , construct , and on , and on , and on , to planet , star system , galaxy , and on to our entire known universe .
would it not be foolish to assume this " mandelbrot " like lattice would stop at the extreem of our meagre ability to observe , rather than continue to follow its serial makeup to unimagined level of structure , and beyond to infinity ( infinity , of course not be a point , but rather a lack of constraint quantifier ) .
