in an article in toronto 's " globe and mail " newspaper , john polanyi , a nobel laureate and member of the department of chemistry at the university of toronto , recommend that afghanistan farmer be allowed( you might even say " be encourage ") to grow poppy ( opium ) legally .
he argue that there be a shortage of painkilling medication , particularly in poor , third world country , and that afghanistan could supply the need poppy at a lower price than commercially produce painkiller .
i see the interview he give on cbc @-@ tv recently and he seem to know what he be talk about .
as he put it : " the afghan farmer have to make a live to fee his - often large - family .
we can force him to produce the poppy illegally and fee into the illegal drug market or we can buy the poppy from him and help provide pain @-@ kill drug ."
