so in the last week , the new head of ofsted , sir michael wilshaw , have say : “ all teacher should be qualify ”.
what an absolutely preposterous suggestion !
you mean to say that , as citizen of this great nation , our children should be teach by professional people who have go through the necessary rigmarole to be let loose in our school ?
how dare we expect that from our education system . and while we 're at it - why stop there ?
let 's round up our homeless and get them work in our hospital .
it 'll get them off the street and straight into promising career .
youth unemployment be rife at the moment so let 's get them pilot our aeroplane .
heathrow might even get its third runway so we could do with a few more pilot .
i hear overcrowd in jail be a problem too - especially since the riot last summer .
why do n't we just convert the miscreant to our side by give them a uniform and a gun ?
they 're bound to see sense and start make our street safe instead of cause the trouble .
and lastly , with the easter holiday come up , young children will need something to keep them occupy .
maybe they can try write for a sunday tabloid - i hear there be vacancy at the sun .
you may have sense my slight sarcastic undertone - although that last suggestion might not be such a bad idea .
call me naive , but i always assume that teacher be either qualify or train alongside someone qualify ?
it seem though that any old sod can do it .
be it any wonder then that the uk 's position in the international league table have slip ?
so despite sound incredibly obvious , mr wilshaw seem to have hit the nail on the head .
problem solve .
i 'm sure it come as a welcome suggestion to all the fully train , out @-@ of @-@ work teacher who struggle to get a job .
not to mention the one who have job and have work extremely hard to get there .
