ok , so i be still learn about how the free market/ global energy supply system work so please correct me if i be wrong , but here be my suggestion ;
all state service include social house , library , hospital , school , prison etc should be power by british energy only and everything the state use ( construction material , food etc ) should be british produce , grow and maintain by a british workforce .
alongside this , we open up the private sector to import and freedom of choice , luxury etc.
the private sector can do pretty much whatever it want but the state must be able to support itself with or without the boom and bust of the private sector .
people who choose to live on benefit ( rely on the state ) will only have access to british resource also .
( british grown ) food will be provide for survival as will house and energy but ( import ) luxury will not be available to those dependent on the state .
if people desire luxury , then they must work for it .
the idea be that the state pay ( modest ) salary for its worker who consume british energy ( retrieve this money through tax from british worker ) and british food/ material .
this would effectively create a system which circulate resource within the country rather than it be channel out into the hand of russian billionaires .
the energy will be supply through wind turbine position offshore around the british isle which be maintain by idle military personnel .
further , a production workforce will be employ by the state in factory to produce say material .
