as a labour party supporter , i disagree with the cut that the coalition government be currently make .
they be go too far , too fast .
their policy of contractionary fiscal policy create a substantial risk of the uk slip back into recession , which mean consumer confidence will begin to fall even further , as people will be more likely to save , which lead to less money be pump into the economy , ie . a fall in aggregate demand .
with current level of unemployment very high , job loss will be the consequence of these harsh , unnecessary cut through the coalition government 's contractionary fiscal policy .
on the other hand , labour 's policy of expansionary fiscal policy mean that although the budget deficit will increase , a significant number of job will be create , aggregate demand will increase , which mean an increase in consumer confidence , therefore household income will increase , which may result in taxpayers move into a higher tax band , which lead to an increase in government revenue from taxation .
if we carry on with the current rate of cut , we will reverse to the 1980 's , make the poorest poor , and the rich rich , same old tories !
cut need to be make at a steady pace , with the budget deficit dealt with once the economy be full steam ahead .
