are you a communist ?
my friend and i walk into a pizza shop .
it be $ 3 a slice .
they have a special , a 12 @-@ slice for $ 10 .
if we both get two slice each , that would make it 4 slice at a total of $ 12 .
we be assure the slice in the 12 @-@ slice be the same size , so we get that .
we each pitch in $ 5 each ( which can n't even buy you two slice oddly enough ) and get 6 slice each , which we 've just polish off in fairly record time .
we pool our resource and struck the better deal for the both of us , and we actually make a joke about proud and full communist .
now we 're roll a joint from a bag of wee we each pitch in on in order to save money as well .
got our usual amount of wee each , but each pay $ 5 less because one of us do the transaction and buy twice as much as usual for the individual .
if these thing make me a communist , than i 'll drink to that , but i just call it better business sense mostly .
real communism would be they could go get a pizza without pay at all , and the pizza guy could come by their auto @-@ part place to pick up a distributor cap without pay at all .
real communism only exist in israel 's kibbutz though .
the problem you be have jason marcel be that it be impossible for many people , and especially people in america , to conceive of cooperation and sacrifice without force behind it .
they be so lock into their little me @-@ centric universe that they can n't see cooperate with someone else unless someone make them .
seriously , i think the problem here be that a lot of people in the u.s. , conservative especially , when they hear the word " communism " think of the soviet union .
not only be the soviet union not communist , it do n't even pretend to be .
the word refers in marxist theory only to the end stage of social progress , what a socialist state and economy evolve into : a stateless utopia in which everything be share equally .
when communism be reach , socialism be no more , because socialism presume the existence of the state , and under communism there be no state .
the motto under socialism be " from each accord to his ability , to each accord to his work." under communism , it 's the more @-@ familiar , " from each accord to his ability , to each accord to his need ."
the soviet union be socialist .
it never pretend to be communist , even though it be govern by something call the communist party .
communism be what they be in theory evolve towards , but certainly not what they already have .
communism be not a coercive system ; it 's the exact opposite .
neither the private coercion of capitalism , nor the state coercion of socialism be find in a communist society .
if it be possible to have a communist society , it would be a wonderful thing .
edit : i answer " no " to the poll , because although communism be a beautiful dream , i consider it no more than that .
