ieds : the lazy man 's insurgency
it 's time to take another look at iraq , because there 's be a big change in insurgent tactic in 2005. that 's inevitable . war make people on both side think faster . peacetime army never learn anything ; wartime army learn new trick faster than a hungry raccoon .
the big change be that the insurgent have decide to rely on ieds rather than ambush with shoulder @-@ fire weapon to kill the two or three gis per day they figure they need to wear down the us public 's will to stay in the fight . and it 's work , way too well .
the stats be clear : ied victim make up a bigger chunk of our casualty every month . over the last six month , ieds have cause 63 % of us combat death . last month ( october 2005 ) be typical : out of 96 us troop kill , ieds be responsible for 57 .
compare that with april 2004 , a terrible month when we lose 140 troop . back then the insurgent relied on rpgs and small arm . only 19 of our 140 kia that month @-@ barely more than a tenth @-@ be kill by ieds .
the insurgent have decide to do it the easy way . as long as they can use ieds , their low @-@ tech standoff weapon , why should they risk close combat ?
the real question be why they can get away with it . and here @-@ well , i hate to keep say this , but somebody need to . the reason they can do it be because we still have no intel on them . it 's the biggest failure of the war , and nobody talk about it . ci warfare be about people , not hardware . we 're all hardware and no intelligence , like a tim allen show . make me sick .
that make the decision to go with ieds a no @-@ brainer for the insurgent . in the standard ambush , the kind we be face a year ago , the insurgent detonate an ied under a convoy , then open up on the stall survivor with rpg and small arm fire . it probably make them feel good , sort of their version of shock and awe , but the rifle fire be ineffective and by concentrate their force , the insurgent make themselves vulnerable to our air power .
the problem in any guerrilla battle be the getaway . anybody can pull a trigger ; the trick be get your men home safe , while enemy chopper zoom through the sky and every street be full of troop and armor look for men of military age . that 's the tough part .
an ied ambush have none of those risk . only one man need to be on the spot @-@ the triggerman . he detonate the ied from a car park down a side street and drive away before the occupier can even start their search . no risk . no casualty . very demoralize for the occupier , especially since they know damn well that everybody in the neighborhood be in on the attack but they can n't level the local ' shack like they 're die to .
what make this wave of ieds worse be that the device be get more effective . frankly i 've be shock at how good the iraqis be with these thing right from the start . i mean , after that shameful performance in gw i , do you expect these bastard to be so sneaky , patient , and smart ? i know this war be a bad idea , but even i never realize what we 'd be up against .
the scariest tech development of all be that the insurgent have learn how to make shape @-@ charge ieds . to understand why shape charge be such a powerful weapon , we have to go into the incredibly cool world of explosive physic . i love this stuff . i mean , what red @-@ blood american boy do n't experiment with explosive ? the only reason i ever open my chem book be to see if it mention tnt or dynamite in the index . ( it do n't @-@ goddamn hippie teachers.) and naturally i use the local wildlife , like toad and bee , in my experiment with the kill power of firecracker .
what i learn be the most important point about the subject : blast alone do n't do a good job of kill the target . a bee would wobble off unhurt after one of my 4 th of july daisycutters go off right next to it .
now before you hothead whose hobby be make pipe bomb in the garage write me angry letter ( or send me long round package with no return address ) , i know a blast can kill , if it 's a big enough blast . we have a really nasty example of that in august this year , when a huge ied kill 14 marine near haditha . from what i 've read , investigation show there be nothing special about the ied . it be just three anti @-@ tank mine stack in a pile @-@ the ihop of ieds , i guess you could call it .
that ambush show real clearly how important intelligence be in guerrilla warfare . the same unit that suffer the ied attack have just have six of its sniper kill in a small @-@ arm ambush . now you tell me how anybody can ambush six sniper unless they 've completely penetrate the unit . the insurgent know where the unit 's sniper would assemble , and they know where the vehicle would be pass . we do n't know a thing about the enemy , but it 's clear that he know way too much about us .
the other problem be that the 14 marine be ride in one of those ridiculous land craft the corps use as apcs @-@ in haditha , hundred of click from the sea ! it 's call the aav @-@ 7a1 , and it look like a giant armored dinghy . since it be design to ferry troop ashore , it sacrifice armor and speed and damn near everything else to an amphibious capability that have no use anymore . but that 's the corps for you . real brave , but not always real smart .
maybe if those guy have be in a real apc some would have survive . i can n't say . if the blast be big enough , it can kill even an mbt . the pal take out two israeli merkavas , the best @-@ armored tank in the world , with simple blast ieds .
but most of the time , guerrilla do n't have the delivery system to depend on blast power . if they 're try to kill soft target @-@ i.e . people @-@ they pack the bomb with homemade shrapnel : roof nail , ball bearing , anything that 'll shred flesh . a suicide vest tip with nail be basically a 360 @-@ degree 12 gauge .
to kill gis that way , you need to catch them off @-@ guard , somewhere they feel safe . that 's what happen when a jihadi kill more than a dozen of our guy in a mess hall in mosul while they be have lunch -- minus their body armor .
in the field , us troop be a hard kill , especially because they move in armored convoy protect by chopper . and that 's the real beauty of ied attack for a guerrilla : they absolutely nullify us air power . there be literally no target for the attack chopper . the pilot know damn well that one of those iraqi car drive away from the scene be carry the guy who set off the ied , but there 's no way to tell which one .
in a strange way , we 're look at a 3d war . we control the air , but the iraqis literally control the underground , thank to these buried ieds . we fly , they dig .
the insurgent ' first ieds be simple . not that there 's anything wrong with simple . the weapon that have be hurt us be all simple , like the rpg . simplicity be the guerrilla 's friend .
those early ieds were usually just shell bury by the road , wire up to a detonator . lot of amateur be tinker in their garage , or whatever iraqis have instead of garage , play with stuff that go boom . and naturally lot of those guy go boom themselves .
like i say , war teach people fast , but some of the lesson have to be learn by the next of kin , not the handyman whose bright idea for a new type of bomb turn him into an abstract paint all over his wall .
sometimes an insurgency have to learn its lesson several time . take the case of pressure @-@ trigger ieds . these be basically standard anti @-@ vehicle mine , with something like a bathroom scale as trigger . people and car can pass over them unharmed , but if a really heavy ( mean armored ) vehicle roll over that scale , the bomb go off . ( truck be a problem . some truck weigh as much as an apc.) the best part be that you do n't even need a triggerman to set it off . you can all be off at the hookah parlor polish up your alibi when it go off .
the insurgent in baqouba use pressure bomb in 2003 , but they usually fail to go off . their bombmakers do n't have the technique yet .
thank to info @-@ share , the internet give an insurgency , they 're back at it , with better wire diagram . a week ago ( oct . 24 ' 05 ) , a pressure bomb shred a humvee in baqouba , tear four gis leg to piece .
the first ieds be mostly mortar round that fail against our armor . so the insurgent go to big 155 mm round . that 's a big , big shell and when you trigger it at the right moment , it 's go to kill almost anything but an m1 .
the m1 be a great tank , so it 's kind of scary to read the stats on how many of them the insurgent have manage to knock out . as usual , the invasion be the easy part and the occupation be when thing get lethal . we only lose 18 m1s in the conventional fight , but the guerrilla have since manage to disable 80. now most of those be track damage , but that 's enough to put a tank out of action .
the good news be that the m1 have live up to its rep for crew protection . the army 's armor center say only five crew have die in ied attack on m1s . ( ten other m1 crow have be kill , mostly by sniper fire , ride in open hatches.)
so if you 're an insurgent bomb @-@ maker , your goal be to find a way to kill m1s . not just knock a tread off , but destroy it and kill the crew . and that 's where the shape @-@ charge ied come in . shape charge be develop for tank kill , use in mbt anti @-@ armor round and antitank weapon . their warhead be basically thick cup of soft metal . metal with low melt point , usually copper . the bomb @-@ maker 's job be to make sure as much of the force of the blast be channeled to the copper cone as possible . so sometimes he 'll put several 155 mm shell beneath the copper , or pack a whole lot of tnt under it .
when the ied detonate , this copper cup turn into a shaft of superheated metal that can zip right through any armor , even an m1 's . that 's what they tell me , and i have to believe it .
it 's the kind of weird science that use to frustrate me in physic , the sort of info you just have to take on faith . i can n't help wonder if they 're kid us civvies about it all . i do n't get why a soft metal like copper can penetrate chobham armor , which can defeat almost any warhead around .
apparently the copper be n't even actually melt . it eject as a solid ; it just " behave like molten metal." i 'm sure the insurgent home improvement tinkerers do n't understand the science involve any more than i do . they just hear that it work and try it out .
the us countermeasure have be pretty lame so far . convoy travel with jammers that make it harder to detonate the ied by cell phone or garage door opener @-@ nokia and genie sale be go to drop in the sunni triangle . but like i say , low @-@ tech be the guerrilla 's friend . these day they 've go back to wire , and i hear some be even use string . you can n't jam a string .
beyond that , bush policy be to blame iran , or syria , or satan or whoever .
iran ? maybe . syria ? no way . syria 's scared to death , ready to do anything to make uncle sam happy . and if it be iran , what can we do about it ? there be still a few neocons so totally out of their little gourd they want us to invade iran . i have to wonder if they 're agent of dr evil , programme to destroy america . because invade iran would do it , it 'd end us once and for all .
this blame stuff be a sign of frustration . nobody know how to stop ieds , even with all the popular mechanic geeks send in their garage @-@ tech brainstorm . that 's because @-@ damn , how many time do i have to repeat it ? -guerrilla war have no technical solution . or even military solution . the only effective ci technique be torture , reprisal and , ultimately , genocide .
my guess be that genocide will come back one day . that be how the ancient dealt with rebellious town : wipe ' em out . one of these day some first @-@ world country be go to get impatient and a problem child like the sunni triangle will be a big , radioactive ghost town .
if we do n't do it , the kurds may end up do it the old @-@ fashion way they learn from the turks : one bullet , one village at a time . it 's be do before -- seen any armenians up there lately ? probably not , but most of " kurdistan " use to be " armenia." a few of the armenians make it to fresno , but the rest be bury up there .
we 're talk about mesopotamia here , the place where war be invent . hundred of people have be wipe out forever in those part . all these holocaust lobbyist get furious if anybody say jews be n't the only tribe to get genocided , but that 's just politics-" our genocide be better than your genocide ! "
the fact be , genocide be , historically , the most common result when one tribe run into another . and something tell me the next big wipeout will happen right there in central iraq .
