a few superficial criticism :
1. it 's not ci ( counter @-@ intelligence ) . ci be when you thwart your enemy 's intel operation . thus , gain intel on when @/@ where the insurgent be plant ieds be intel , not counter @-@ intel .
2. iraqis do n't have garage at their house . thus , i would conclude that this guy have never step foot in iraq .
some meaty criticism :
1. the marine 's aav be as armored as the standard army apc - the m113. it sound as if this pundit be probably a former army guy . based on the damage to the single aav that be involve , unless it be a m @-@ 1 , more armor would n't have help . that 's how big the ieds be get .
2. a single 155 mm round do n't do any significant damage to us armored vehicle ( the up @-@ armored hmmwv be n't a true armored vehicle in the sense that it be design from the ground up with armor in mind - it be modify from a cargo vehicle ) . for example , on the stryker , a 155 mm round will scratch some paint off and flatten tire .
3. war be like a sport . it be interactive and tactic , technique , and procedure evolve continuously in reaction to your opponent . back to the sport analogy , if you 're get kill in a zone defense , you switch to man @-@ to @-@ man , etc. he seem to apply a template that the enemy of the us should be dumb and not react . underestimate your enemy be a bad and dumb thing to do .
4. he fail to mention the intel that we get that allow us to defuse the majority of ieds before they be detonate .
5. he fail to mention how switch back to wire device make it easier to catch the trigger man .
6. he fail to mention how use larger device mean that you need to spend more time prepare the site , which mean a greater chance of compromise .
7. he complain about intel , but then advocate harsh technique that run contrary to the value of the us and do n't weigh the impact that these technique would have on gain intel from the population and @/@ or bring the population off the fence and to our side . his recommendation would result be less intelligence - gain some information from a pay triggerman may result in a few short @-@ term success within a particular cell , but it will alienate the population and result be less intel over the long @-@ run from the population and future cell that would be create down the road due the increase perception of occupation through the harsh technique he advocate . as an example , abu ghraib , which be the direct result of a half @-@ dozen irresponsible individual that be able to conduct their abuse due to the lack leadership of their supervisor , have a huge negative impact on our relation with local iraqis . the trust we have build with many be erode and our ability to gain trust with others be much more challenge .
bottomline , he do n't truly analyze the situation from all aspect and use some faulty assumption and some fact that be flat out wrong . in the end , you have the action @-@ reaction @-@ counteraction cycle that be produce bigger ieds that be easier to catch , but more deadly if you do n't catch it . i 'm not state that it 's not a problem , but this analysis do n't offer much value .
i hope this help . as far approach to coin , i 'm sure that ray , lemontree , dave angel , and some of the others on this board whose militaries have be do coin for much longer than the us ( which , btw have do coin quite frequently , but then shun it as a freak occurance and do n't internalize the lesson learn in favor on focusing on the " big threat ") can comment at length on why this article espouse the wrong approach to the problem .
