first off a little info..
marshall amplification have be one of the lead guitar amplifier company for 50 year .
many of the older amp be be restore and also there be countless company offer clone and cloned replacement part for diy'ers .
since i like wood work i think some folk would enjoy an amplifier shell that they could finish themselves and either use it to restore an old marshall amplifier or to collect aftermarket part from countless other vendor and end up with a vintage marshall clone .
so , i have have pretty good luck sell these wooden amp head shell in the past and think i would reintroduce my product .
well , ebay pull my list for have the word " marshall " in the title .
my actual list read " marshall style plexi @/@ jcm800 headshell for project ."
notice the word " style ".
i do a quick ebay search use " marshall style " and come up with 100 's of listings that use that term for after market part and kit .
the listings i click on be not actaul marshall product .
i also search another famous amplifier company and type in " fender style ".
again 100 's of listings for aftermarket part and kit .
why be i singled out when there be 1,000 's and 1,000 's of people list this way ?
and its clear that i do not claim it be an actual " marshall " product which be why i put the word " style " in the list .
do not seem right .
people who be look for these item won't find them without know that it be for a marshall or marshall style amp .
i love the smell of package tape in the morning .
can n't use the manufacturer 's name in the title unless the item be list be actually make by the manufacturer .
ebay rule - not mine .
michael 's right - someone somewhere decide to report you , and you end up get a wrist @-@ slap .
you -@ could @- start report all the " style " listings you find and ( hopefully ) watch them go away .
sometimes it only take one report... sometimes you gotta stay on top of it for a while .
there be special rule for what you want to do , offer non @-@ brand replacement component ( in your case , the wood case ) .
unfortunately , i just do n't recall what they all are...
there 's a way to word the description that work and do n't get you slap for " keyword spamming " ( which be what put marshall in the descriptive text will earn you ) .
fun stuff , eh ?
