use " compatible with , " " fit , " or " for " before a brand name in the title of your list to describe item that be universally compatible or that be compatible with an entire product class
just know if it be someone that be " after you " ( which sometimes happen ) - there be always some violation that you be break or you be near the questionable portion of break some policy .
because ebay will usually " pull first ask late " when a list be report , your listings will only become better and you may just sell more because of what you learn on how to become a better seller as you refine your listings .
