now , this be originally take out as interest only but when i 've phone a couple of year ago to increase the payment they have change it to " part interest , part repayment ". not too fuss about this as i 've work out the number and the correct amount be come off the capital every month .
i 'm go to contact halifax for detail on how to make overpayments as i 've increase my direct debit again but would like to be able to make ad @-@ hoc overpayments when i 'm able to .
thing i 'm curious about be the 10 % overpayment thing - i know my mortgage agreement be subject to this however what do it really mean ? should i only be pay 10 % more than my interest only payment or be it 10 % extra off the capital ? my new direct debit ( as of end dec 12 would take me over the 10 % of io payment ) .
i 'm guess they will give me a rough idea of how much i can overpay in £s based on my current direct debit but would be interested to know beforehand just for my knowledge .
