its 10 % of the mortgage balance for the year , so if your mortgage balance in £100,000 that year you can overpay by £10,000 during the course of the year without penalty .
however , if you be on the svr you dont have the 10 % limit , just overpay as much as you can comfortably afford
quote :
are you sure you 're on svr ? or just a rate that be soon to end ?
have work for halifax it be indeed correct that once you 've reach the svr then no overpayment limit be enforce you be simply free to overpay as much as you wish to .
this be correct . your kfi @/@ mortgage offer may say something along the line of ' in any one year you may repay up to 10 % of the amount outstanding on your special rate product '. it 's a roll 12 month , so the year start when you make your 1 st overpayment . so , you could n't pay £10k in december and another £10k in january for instance , you 'd need to wait 12 month .
then , once your ' special rate product ' end , you go onto svr , with no overpayment restriction .
