tajikistan ( tj ) ; afghanistan ( af )
international ; narcotic
the number of heroin addict in tajikistan have vastly increase over the past five year due to drug traffic between afghanistan and russia and europe .
the number of heroin addict in tajikistan have vastly increase over the past five year due to drug traffic between afghanistan and europe .
the majority of the heroin be grow in neighboring afghanistan .
afghanistan be the world 's top opium producer .
tajikistan share a 1300 @-@ kilometer ( 800 @-@ mile ) border with afghanistan and have become a transit point for heroin be traffic into russia and europe .
in 2001 the russian army and tajik police confiscate nearly 9 ton of drug and arrest more than 2000 people .
the russian army guard tajikistan 's border with afghanistan .
the majority of tajikistan 's heroin addict live in city and be age between 18 and 25 .
75 percent of tajikistan 's population life in rural area , where heroin addict be frequently ostracize .
head of a public drug clinic in dushanbe , tajikistan andrei onishchenko , state --
there be 5000 heroin addict officially register in tajikistan , compare with 57 in 1997 .
the actual figure be seven time greater than the official number .
the low cost and availability of heroin be among the cause of the addiction problem .
one dose of heroin cost less than a dollar in tajikistan , which be less than the price of a bottle of the local vodka .
an addict who have be use heroin for 2 year need to use 3 gram of heroin every 24 hour .
3 gram of heroin cost 70 somonis or 30 dollar .
an addict be willing to commit any crime to pay for heroin .
afghan heroin be the strongest in the world because it be make from poppy cultivate at high altitude and therefore subject to high dose of ultra @-@ violet light .
a person who take a daily dose of afghan heroin have a life expectancy of between 5 and 7 year and many commit suicide before that .
the tajik state pay 25 dirams ( a few cent ) per day for every person in the rehabilitation clinic .
the percentage of relapse be very high due to the lack of followup treatment and unemployment among young people .
head of a tajik government agency that fight drug traffic avaz yuldachev state that heroin user be ill and need treatment .
anvar , a 14 @-@ year @-@ old boy from dushanbe , use heroin for three year before be hospitalize in onishchenko 's drug clinic .
anvar say --
he sniff a white substance he find in his backyard and be unable to stop .
he stop go to school .
he steal from the local market to get money for more heroin .
drug trafficker face the death penalty under tajik law .
tajikistan have 6.2 million inhabitant .
