russia ( ru ) ; iran ( ir )
international ; government ; weapon ; technology ; proliferation
ecological organization greenpeace state on june 21 , 2002 that russia help iran to develop nuclear weapon by build iran 's bushehr atomic power station .
the russian branch of greenpeace distribute a report at a press conference of russia 's atomic energy ministry .
the ministry concede that the russo @-@ iranian accord on the plant 's construction do not require the repatriation of the nuclear fuel .
the report state that the recycle of nuclear fuel from bushehr be not mention in the accord between the russian and iranian government on the construction of the plant .
greenpeace member vladimir chuprov say the ministry have practically admit that iran will not return to russia the spent nuclear fuel from the power station and russia 's only use for iran be to equip itself with nuclear weapon .
the atomic energy ministry confirm the report 's existence and strongly deny greenpeace 's accusation .
ministry spokesman nikolai shingarev tell afp that russia would only supply nuclear fuel to iran on condition that it be return to russia after its use .
shingarev say russia be currently in negotiation with iran .
this issue will be settle before the power station come into operation .
shingarev say the accord on bushehr be sign before russia pass a law permit the import of nuclear waste last year .
this explain why the accord make no mention of the return of the fuel .
shingarev say it be very difficult to make a nuclear weapon from the plutonium in this fuel .
the unite state and israel fear that the russian @-@ iranian nuclear cooperation could enable tehran to acquire the technology need to build nuclear weapon .
russia dismiss this accusation .
iran order the power station in 1994 at a cost of nearly 800 million dollar ( 860 million euros ) from russia .
iran have say the plant be be build only for civilian energy purpose and allow regular inspection of bushehr by the international atomic energy agency .
expert say bushehr could in theory become operational as early as september 2003 .
currently it be equip with a single reactor .
german group siemens pull out of the long @-@ stand project at the request of the german government after iran 's 1979 islamic revolution .
us president george w. bush raise the us 's concern about russian nuclear cooperation with iran at the summit in moscow last month between bush and his russian counterpart vladimir putin .
