iraq ( iq )
proliferation ; international
atomic energy agency director state it would be difficult for iraq to conceal a nuclear weapon program if international inspector be allow to return .
inspector would perform various test , visit , and interview and their presence alone in the country would be a deterrent .
on 18 october 2002 international atomic energy agency ( iaea ) director mohamed elbaradei state it be unlikely that iraq could conceal a nuclear weapon program if it allow international inspector to return .
elbaradei state that once inspector be work in iraq their presence alone would be a deterrent to develop nuclear weapon .
elbaradei state to reporter at his headquarters in vienna --
it be difficult to conceal a nuclear program if thorough inspection be perform because nuclear product always have a signature .
trace be always visible if highly enrich uranium or plutonium be use .
elbaradei state that inspector would perform environmental sample , gamma radiation survey from helicopter , internal periodic visit to all capable site and interview with all former nuclear scientist to confirm that they be not work in the nuclear program .
elbaradei state that the iaea could not give a 100 percent guarantee but that the presence of inspector would be a good deterrent and a good mechanism for detection .
elbaradei state --
it be necessary to control import to iraq because of the risk that iraq be receive nuclear material from outside the country .
there must be physical protection of all nuclear material particularly in the former soviet union .
there must be strong unanimous support by the un security council to force iraq to comply with iaea inspection .
the iaea must be give as much intelligence information as possible to guide inspector to anything that should be inspect or to any item hidden from inspector .
the security council have be meet in open session to discuss the iraq issue before the vote on condition under which un weapon inspector will return to baghdad to verify iraqi assertion that it do not possess nuclear , chemical or biological weapon .
un weapon inspector depart baghdad in 1998 .
