a u.s. study release on 03 december 2002 state that one @-@ tenth of the internet 's site may be block by chinese authority as part of effort to prevent access to information on dissident , taiwan , tibet and other subject .
the study be conduct by harvard university 's berkman center for internet and society .
the study find that more than 50000 of the approximately 200000 websites test be inaccessible from at least 1 point in china on at least 1 occasion .
use a more narrow definition of block site the study conclude that 18931 websites be be block to chinese web user .
harvard researcher and co @-@ author of the report ben edelman state that it be likely that similar percentage apply to the internet as a whole .
edelman tell afp that it be highly likely that approximately one @-@ tenth of the internet be filter by or recently have be filter by china .
edelman state that there be many different way to measure this effect and therefore hesitate to specify any single proportion .
the latest study be broader than prior survey and give perspective to disparate report about websites that be filter or block by china .
in the report it be conclude that --
china block a range of web content beyond that which be sexually explicit .
1000 s of site provide information about news , health , education , and entertainment be block .
approximately 3284 site from taiwan be block .
the block site also include those of u.s. news organization include abc news and cbs news , the alta vista search engine , and a number of u.s. university .
the researcher find that 100 percent of the top 10 site with keywords tibet , taiwan china , or equality be block .
a large number of other site with keywords such as freedom , democracy and hiv be also block .
the bbc news site be consistently unavailable .
site for cnn , time magazine , u.s. @-@ based public broadcast system , the miami herald , and the philadelphia inquirer be also often block .
the report find that 42 of google 's top 100 result for news be block .
religious site block in china include the asian american baptist church , the atheist network , the catholic civil right league , feng shui , the jewish federation of winnipeg , and the denver zen center .
china have an estimate 45 million internet user .
china have be widely criticize in the west for block websites and for imprison people for view ban site or use the internet for anti @-@ government activity .
the chinese government be believe to routinely block a large number of foreign @-@ based site primarily those feature dissident view or ban group such as the falungong spiritual organization but also certain foreign news site and page show pornography .
a recent report by the u.s. @-@ based rand corporation think tank find that the chinese government now use more technology to filter out objectionable content rather than relying solely on surveillance of user and seizure of equipment as it do in the past .
the rand report release earlier in 2002 found that chinese authority now appear to have more effective technology for filter out undesirable content .
