2003 @-@ 03 @-@ 30
thailand ( th ) ; myanmar ( mm )
international ; narcotic
the methamphetamine pill know as yaa baa have surpass heroin as thailand 's number one killer drug .
several million thai people use the drug .
the methamphetamine pill know as yaa baa have surpass heroin as thailand 's number one killer drug .
several million thai people use the drug .
the pill have become part of thai society .
no other drug have become as integral in decade .
the effect on the brain of its consumer be disastrous .
yaa baa be know as crazy medicine in thailand .
it have be targeted in a two @-@ month anti @-@ drug crackdown that have result in the death of nearly 1,900 suspect trafficker .
there be much concern over the drug .
the drug 's popularity increase in the mid @-@ 1990 s .
it have make thailand the world 's number one consumer .
pierre @-@ arnaud chouvy and joel meissonnier state in their book yaa baa recently publish by the institute of research on contemporary southeast asia that the psychotropic drug be use across society for both work and pleasure .
construction worker , sailor , farmer and taxi driver take the drug to help them through long work day .
student use it to get through exam period .
clubbers use it to help them dance all night .
yaa baa possess several quality that have help it supplant heroin as the drug of choice in thailand .
the book state that the drug convey a completely positive image .
it appear modern and inoffensive because it be synthetic .
the energy , confidence and euphoric feel have give user an image as a drug of happiness .
the pill can also be easily consume .
they can be pop or dissolve in a glass of water , take intravenously , pulverize and inhale , or smoke .
there be at least 90 type of the pill .
yaa baa be easy to manufacture and do not have any climate uncertainty like other drug have .
instruction on how to manufacture the drug be available on the internet .
heroin require opium poppy as its raw ingredient and cocaine depends on yield from the coca plant .
the drug have an affordable price .
it cost 60 baht ( 1.50 dollar ) per pill on the street before thailand 's drug war start on february 1 , 2003 and push the price up 300 percent .
the pill cost five @-@ cent to produce .
800 million pill enter thailand from myanmar last year .
the book state that the majority of the drug come from myanmar particularly the area control by the wa of the uwsa ( unite wa state army ) .
the book be referring to the pro @-@ yangon ethnic group say to operate around 50 laboratory close to the border and the mobile production unit .
myanmar could become an unrivaled regional producer because of the link between the military ruler and the uwsa , and the jungle canopy where uwsa operate .
the military and uwsa link result in a lack of law enforcement .
the drug have become a specialty of the golden triangle where thailand , laos and myanmar converge .
much of the world 's opium be still produce there .
chouvy and meissonnier say that methamphetamine be overtake heroin as the production drug of choice in the area and be profit enormously from the distribution network that heroin traffic have already establish .
five percent of thailand 's population be now estimate to abuse methamphetamine .
the international narcotic control bureau say the figure make it the largest per capita consumer in the world .
the drug have be around in other form for year .
it be first use in the 1920 s as an antidepressant and then as a psychostimulant during world war ii and the vietnam war .
people recruit from impoverished ethnic minority transport the pill along a multitude of route .
myanmar soldier and thai police and bureaucrat protect the cargo and allow them to eventually reach consumer in thailand .
the book state that one pill will pass through seven intermediary from the frontier runner to the retailer .
the retailer will usually sell more to the drug user than he or she require .
this create another dealer and explain the drug 's easy availability across thailand .
owner of boat in the southern coastal province of ranong and construction foremen in bangkok be know to force their worker to take the drug at the begin of the workday .
occasionally in rural area the farmer dissolve the drug in a bottle which they drink while work .
consumer be as young as seven and school have become one of the main hub for traffic of methamphetamine .
thailand 's youth be the most at risk .
