expert state the preparatory session can not change the treaty but be expect to focus on problem in fight proliferation and in get the 5 original nuclear weapon state to fulfill the npt commitment to disarm .
a conference on the world 's nuclear non @-@ proliferation treaty ( npt ) against the spread of nuclear weapon open on 30 april 2007 in vienna .
the meet will take place through 14 may 2007 and be the 1 st of a series of preparatory committee session ahead of the next overall review in 2010 .
the npt go into effect at the height of the cold war in 1970 and be extend indefinitely in 1995 .
the npt have 188 signatory state and be a deal in which nuclear weapon state agree to disarm while nation without the bomb agree not to seek the bomb .
the npt be review every 5 year .
the meet in may 2005 fail to resolve any key question due to an agenda disagreement between non @-@ align country and nuclear power .
the npt conference occur as --
the crisis over iran 's atomic program escalate though iran have not yet produce atomic bomb .
a deal to dismantle north korea 's nuclear program which have produce atomic bomb have stall .
a u.s. strategy to use pre @-@ emptive force if judged necessary and britian 's nuclear arsenal upgrade threaten the npt .
expert state the npt be ill adapt to the modern era in which so @-@ call rogue state seek to acquire a nuclear weapon capacity by 1 st develop peaceful programs under the term of the treaty .
expert state that fix should include tougher un inspection and automatic penalty for country who drop out of the treaty .
the north korean government withdraw from the npt in 2003 after expel unite nation inspector .
the north korean government test an atomic bomb in october 2006 .
the iranian government justify nuclear work under article iv of the npt which guarantee the inalienable right to develop research , production and use of nuclear energy for peaceful purpose .
u.s. government state that the iranian government use article iv as a cover for the secret development of nuclear weapon which the treaty ban .
non @-@ proliferation analyst at the carnegie endowment for international peace in washington george perkovich state the npt be the most effective treaty in history and referred to the fact that prediction make in the 1960 s that there would soon be 30 @-@ 40 nuclear weapon state have not come to pass .
there be believe to be 9 nuclear weapon state .
the state be the 5 allow under the npt , britain , china , france , russia and the unite state .
the state also include north korea which withdraw from the treaty and 3 nuclear state include india , pakistan and israel which have refuse to sign the npt .
diplomat and expert state the preparatory session can not change the treaty but be expect to focus on problem in fight proliferation and in get the 5 original nuclear weapon state to fulfill the npt commitment to disarm which be a focus of non @-@ align state .
nuclear and disarmement expert rebecca johnson write the week of 22 april 2007 on johnson 's acronym institute website that the risk of nuclear proliferation be too grave for the international community to shirk responsibility and that the npt have already begin to unravel .
felicity hill of the non @-@ governmental organization the international campaign to abolish nuclear weapon ( ican ) state to afp that the meet could build towards a successful 2010 review conference but progress must occur on both non @-@ proliferation and disarmament .
a diplomat in vienna who closely follow the non @-@ proliferation regime state that expectation be be lower for a successful outcome to the preparatory committee given the inauspicious international development and the grow detritus of arm control agreement cast aside .
