on 16 may 2002 malaysia 's deputy home affair minister chor chee heung tell delegate from the region that leader of southeast asian country should consider standardize domestic law and should introduce new law to aid the effort against terrorism and cross @-@ border crime .
chor make the statement at a meet of senior police and official from the law and order ministry of the association of southeast asian nation , or asean .
asean member be malaysia , singapore , indonesia , the philippines , thailand , brunei , laos , cambodia , vietnam and myanmar .
the 2 @-@ day asean conference focused on fight sea piracy , gun smuggle , drug traffic , illegal immigration and other cross @-@ border crime .
chor state the pace of technological improvement be rapidly outstrip the ability of law enforcement agency to keep pace with transnational criminal organization .
chor state the recent communication development have aid cross @-@ border money launder , illegal gamble and electronic fraud .
chor state that forge extradition treaty , standardize definition of crime , simplify law on the seizure of criminal proceed and introduce similar witness protection programs would be beneficial .
chor state harmonization of law will spread the risk that criminal organization have to confront and provide fewer safe haven for transnational organized crime organization .
some official state the task would be difficult for asean member because of vary legal and political system .
deputy commissioner of the royal palace thai police 's special branch amarin neemskul state standardize law in southeast asia be not currently possible though the willingness be there .
asean official will hold separate talk on combating terrorism immediately after the conference in kuala lumpur , malaysia .
