cuba ( cu )
international ; technology ; business ; money ; health ; science ; economy ; government
cuban biotechnology pharmaceuticals program seek to expand to overseas market in develop country .
the cuban government seek to increase pharmaceutical profit by significantly expand overseas market through the development of novel pharmaceuticals and the sale of the world 's most lucrative biotechnology drug , erythropoetin ( epo ) .
amgen inc. invent epo and share patent right with johnson & johnson and kirin brewery in the most lucrative industrialized market -- the us , europe and japan .
in 2001 epo generate 6 billion dollar in sale for the 3 corporation .
amgen sell epo in the us as epogen for over 36 dollar per dose .
us epogen consumer pay over 10000 dollar each annually for the drug .
epo be a genetically engineer protein use legally by kidney dialysis and chemotherapy patient and illegally by athlete to increase the concentration of oxygenate red blood cell .
an increase quantity of biotechnology drug be produce without any attempt to obtain license in develop nation .
us patent holder consider the trade in generic drug a violation to their intellectual property .
consumer in develop country appreciate lower price on generic drug .
cuba consider the generic drug trade good business and currently manufacture epo for sale in argentina , brazil , india and other country that do not acknowledge most us and european drug patent .
cuban biotechnology executive blanca tormo state that cuba carefully abide by intellectual property law and exclusively sell epo in country in which no entity have exclusive patent right .
the largest potential pharmaceutical market be in the 1.3 billion person chinese market .
amgen , kirin , the small canadian biotechnology company dragon pharmaceuticals inc. and at lease 4 chinese company currently sell epo in china .
the generic product cost as low as 5 dollar per dose in china .
by join the world trade organization in 2001 china agree to abide by wto intellectual property agreement but the agreement contain mechanism allow develop nation to circumvent patent , particularly in pharmaceuticals , when public health concern be deem to override the patent .
current state of biotechnology in cuba --
the cuban biotechnology industry currently generate 100 million dollar annually and reach market in over 40 country .
cuba 's genetic engineer and biotechnology center occupy modern tower approve by fidel castro and employ over 1000 people to engineer protein to combat major terminal illness .
cuba currently produce novel biotechnology product : hepatitis b and meningitis b vaccine , a skin growth factor , interferons , thrombosis and heart attack medicine and aid treatment .
cuba have produce over 78 million dose of hepatitis b vaccine .
cuba license its meningitis b vaccine to the british company glaxosmithkline , which hope to eventually sell the vaccine in the unite state under a clinton @-@ era exemption to the cuban trade embargo .
cuba be cooperate with the small canadian company ym biosciences on trial of a head and neck cancer treatment .
cuba be seek further partnership with foreign company in vaccine research for aid , 8 type of cancer and cholera .
cuban official include attendees of the annual bio 2002 industry conference 20020600 in toronto state that negotiation for new biotechnology trade and production agreement be in progress with brazil , malaysia , netherlands , spain , mexico , venezuela , vietnam , ukraine , germany and the unite state .
cuba have or be negotiate technology transfer agreement with 14 country , chiefly develop nation include india , algeria and south africa .
20020500 us undersecretary of state for arm control john bolton state that the us believe cuba have at least a limited offensive biological warfare research and development effort and have provide dual @-@ use biotechnology to other rogue state .
scientist , castro , and former us president jimmy carter , who visit cuba directly after bolton 's statement , dismiss bolton 's statement as unfair .
tormo state that bolton unintentionally increase publicity for the cuban biotechnology program .
