russia ( ru )
international ; government ; technology ; military ; space
russian military space force put on test duty an optical space @-@ object track facility locate in the ex @-@ soviet republic of tajikistan
the russian military space force on 020718 inaugurate an optical track facility that be intend to monitor object in space and put it on test duty .
the okno optical track facility be near the town of nurek in the central region of the ex @-@ soviet republic of tajikistan and locate 50 kilometers ( 30 mile ) southeast of the tajik capital dushanbe .
russian space force say in a statement carry by the interfax @-@ military news agency that the okno ( window ) complex be capable of track object 40000 kilometers ( 24800 mile ) from earth .
the okno offer a better range and precision than standard radar facility accord to the space force .
the report do not elaborate on how the okno work .
the report saids space force chief col . @-@ gen . anatoly perminov traveled to the site to report on the facility 's launch to defense minister sergei ivanov , .
accord to image on the federation of american scientist ' web site , the facility involve telescope @-@ like equipment house in several large sphere .
the okno be locate in tajikistan 's mountain 2200 meter ( 7260 feet ) above sea level and take advantage of the area 's fine weather and high transparency of the atmosphere .
such condition be not find elsewhere in the former soviet union .
the site describe it as similar to the u.s. geodss system , or ground @-@ based electro @-@ optical deep space surveillance .
three such u.s. facility be operational .
the construction of the facility start in 790000 , but stop after the 910000 soviet collapse when tajikistan slide into a 5 year civil war that undermined its economy and leave its population in deep poverty .
about 25000 russian troop and border guard be deploy in tajikistan to help protect its volatile southern border with afghanistan and prevent drug smuggle .
