italy ( it )
international ; telecom ; business ; government ; technology ; politics
italy be lead a technology transfer initiative develop by the g @-@ 8 country which will improve the technology of develop country .
the goal of the initiative be to provide the infrastructure and good governance need to alleviate poverty .
italy sponsor technology transfer to develop country as a form of foreign aid and alleviate poverty .
premier silvio berlusconi support and sponsor the initiative with counterpart at recent international gathering include the last g @-@ 8 summit in canada .
italy persuade partner to let italy lead the g @-@ 8 summit 's e @-@ government initiative call dot force or digital opportunity task force .
former ibm executive and current technology minister of italy lucio stanca be lead italy 's internet program for develop country as part of the group of eight 's effort to reduce the digital divide .
silvio berlusconi give lucio stanca his current role of modernize italy 's bureaucracy .
lucio stanca state that italy will not targeting country that have very basic need .
the first technology transfer project will be implement in the fall .
one such project be create an electronic database for real estate in mozambique .
so far 12 million euros or 12 million dollar have be allocate to finance the initial phase of these project .
this cost be only a fraction of the total cost .
italy be finance most of the cost but the world bank and possibly some private telecommunications company be also contribute .
lucio stanca state that the world must solve the problem of world hunger , disease and education but in order to do that the world must first help create good governance .
the rationale behind create good governance be that by make the public administration of develop country more transparent and accountable develop country would become more attractive potential recipient of traditional form of aid such as loan and investment .
in effect good governance would invalidate the reason use by country that do not do enough that donate be not appropriate because it be impossible to know whether the aid would reach its true destination .
the unite nation telecommunications agency state that 83 country in africa , asia , and the former soviet union still have less than 10 telephone line for every 100 people .
other study note that even though the internet have be in use for more than a decade , only about 10 percent of the world 's population have access to it .
reduce the digital divide have take on a central role in the fight against global poverty in recent year .
the unite nation have repeatedly state that the world 's poor may be further marginalized if there be no improvement in access to information technology .
reduce the digital divide be declare a priority at last year 's g @-@ 8 summit in genoa which include russia .
italy launch pilot programs in 5 country at a conference in sicily sponsor by the unite nation and italy in april , 2002 .
the conference focused on how technology can be use to improve administration in develop country .
the plan for albania be computerization of demographic survey .
the plan for jordan be e @-@ procurement which will allow online trade , auction , payment and settlement of bill .
the plan for tunisia be the creation of electronic databases to facilitate tax collection .
the plan for nigeria and mozambique be the creation an electronic database for real estate .
washington @-@ based adviser at world learn ann hudock state that poverty reduction will only occur when the poor themselves be bring into the policy process .
oxfram america be a nonprofit development group based in boston .
world learn be an organization promote education and justice .
