china ( cn )
international ; weapon ; technology ; government ; proliferation
a lead arm expert state that china 's improve nuclear arsenal raise question about the chinese government 's future arm control effort .
the expert praise beijing official for decrease sale of weapon abroad .
a lead arm expert state on 8 may 2008 that chinese government be make dramatic improvement to china 's nuclear arsenal which raise question for future arm control effort .
director of the stockholm international peace research institute bate gill spoke at a panel for journalist while on a visit to beijing to promote an annual report on the global arm industry .
gill state --
recent upgrade have increase the accuracy and mobility of china 's arsenal while a switch from liquid to solid fuel have shorten reaction time .
china stand out due to the effort to modernize , expand and improve nuclear weapon capability .
among the 5 nuclear power china be make the most dramatic improvement in nuclear force which raise arm control question .
the chinese government state china will never be the first to use nuclear weapon in a conflict and china 's arsenal , estimate at just over 100 nuclear @-@ arm missile , be the smallest of the 5 main nuclear weapon power .
chinese official sign the nuclear nonproliferation treaty in 1992 and gill state the recent step be aim mainly at reduce the vulnerability of china 's deterrent force .
gill state that improvement in china 's conventional military be even more dramatic after more than 10 year of double @-@ digit percentage increase in annual defense spend .
gill state the large increase in the military capability of china be targeted mostly at taiwan but have the possibility go forward with force projection elsewhere .
taiwan be a self @-@ govern island that china claim be part of china 's territory and have threaten to invade .
gill state that the increase in military capability complicate the issue of china as a player in the arm control agenda and that the chinese government would need to be engage in future effort to cap or reduce number of nuclear weapon .
gill praise beijing official for decrease sale of weapon and military technology abroad which gill believe be largely do out of a desire to be view as a more responsible player in international society .
accord to the stockholm international peace research institute china have only a 2 percent share of the global arm export trade .
gill state that the shift in the way the chinese government view the problem of nonproliferation be very positive .
gill state that authority need to strengthen regulation to prevent weapon from enter conflict zone , particularly in africa where chinese arm be use by both government and rebel force in sudan 's darfur region .
retire people 's liberation army colonel teng jianqun spoke alongside gill on the panel and state that china have substantial restriction on weapon sale abroad .
teng concede that some dealer violate the rule and be beyond the government 's direct control .
teng state that further step be be take to boost awareness of the rule , partly through course for government and defense industry leader run by the foreign ministry @-@ sponsor china arm control and disarmament association of which teng be deputy secretary @-@ general .
teng state a belief that the chinese have be put more effort into export control .
