guo kai 's economic note : your uncle be just your uncle .
guo kai 's economic note
this morning i go to the supermarket with dad , and when it come time to check out i discover something that everybody probably know : not everybody buy the same thing .
of course this be a no - brainer , but this be actually a major problem face by me and many other people whenever we discuss economic issue or economic phenomena .
most of the time , economic policy and economic theory be not aim at individual .
in term of probability , if you explain the behavior of a specific individual , for example your uncle , use any economic theory , the probability that it will be accurate be virtually 0 .
in fact , in the great majority of case the economic theory be aim at an entire group , or a subgroup .
in term of average , accuracy be the goal of many economic theory ( here i 'm be inaccurate ; i hope the expert will not take it too literally , especially those with io expertise ) .
but with regard to an ordinary person , he may never see the whole group , he see only his co @-@ worker , his relative and his friend , the group of people familiar to him ; add up all the people in this group and they may number 200 , and that be already a lot of people .
below i be go to refer to these 200 people collectively as " his uncle . "
so whenever you discuss an economic theory with someone , the response of a perfectly ordinary person would be : my uncle be n't like that , so this theory be baloney .
in other word , everybody tend to mistake the part for the whole .
here , mistake the part for the whole be not derogatory ; it be a limitation of the human race itself ; you have it and i have it .
if americans have learn not to mistake the part for the whole , they might not have make such a mess of the world .
i believe that they make such a complete mess of the middle east to a very large extent because they apply their own common sense to understand the middle east , which be a completely different place from the unite state .
on this issue , china do not have much basis for be self - congratulatory ; china 's rapid rise have even cause some people to have a sort of misconception - that whatever china do be right - and this be in fact a manifestation of narrow - mindedness .
therefore i believe it be extremely important to recognize that one 's own knowledge have limitation .
we need to maintain a sufficiently open attitude toward thing that do n't correspond to our common sense .
so just because every time your uncle go to the supermarket he buy hog head meat do n't mean that we should immediately assume that any theory that do not predict people go to the supermarket will buy hog head meat be wrong .
when you feel other people be talk baloney , and what other people say do not correspond to your " common sense , " you should at the same time recognize that your uncle be only your uncle , he be not the whole world .
well , gasoline in richmond have have hit $ 3.00 a gallon , or just shy of it ,
and i spend $ 48 fill up the gas tank of my jeep --
the most i 've ever pay for in my life .
i 'm not happy about it ,
but i do n't see high gas price as a reason to start foam at the mouth and chew on the carpet .
others feel less constrain .
the hysteria over rise gas price have reach a fever pitch .
the economic ignorance of the sound bite and commentary i 've see on national television know no bound .
demagogue be call for self - destructive tax on oil company profit , oblivious to the reality that , in a capitalist society , profit be a critical signal that guide the flow of capital .
( 1 ) if you confiscate exxon mobil 's profit , you reduce the capital available to the world 's largest oil company to invest in more exploratory drill , new oil well , new pipeline , new refinery , etc.
( 2 ) if you tax oil industry profit , you also reduce the incentive for owner of outside capital to invest in new capacity .
why bother if the profit will be tax away ?
