what the political and business leadership of virginia have so far fail utterly to do be admit that virginia be acutely vulnerable to oil price shock .
virginians consume more gasoline per capita than the national average , in part because our transportation policy be gear toward matching every increase in automobile travel with an increase in transportation capacity with no thought of modulate travel demand .
