if you 're arlington county , you create a new vision for the boxy building and subterranean passageway in crystal city that will be empty by the federal base realignment and closure commission .
in place of the sterile monoculture that now characterize the office complex near the pentagon , member of an advisory task force see a more lively street - level scene with a greater mix of shop , restaurant and office .
write wapo reporter annie gowen :
[ board of supervisor chairman chris ] zimmerman and others speak yesterday say that the vounty see the empty space as an opportunity to `` reimagine '' and `` brand '' crystal city as an attractive destination .
though close to reagan national airport and dense with hotel , the area have long be see as a gloomy 1960 s era enclave of office connect by underground passage .
but part of crystal city have lately see a rebirth , thank to an influx of trendy cafe and a new streetscape ....
charles e. smith commercial realty , which own 7.4 million of the 11 million square feet of office space in the neighborhood , have spend $ 40 million on improvement to enliven the street and attract new business .
it turn crystal drive into a two - way main street and have recruit new shop and chic restaurant such as jaleo and mccormick & schmick 's .
read between the line of gowen 's story , however , there seem to be one big miss piece :
house .
create a livelier commercial district be a worthy goal .
but create a balanced community with a mix of house , office , shop and other amenity -- allow people to live close to where they work and play -- be an even more worthy goal .
as ed risse have point out , the relocation of 17,000 job create a rare opportunity to create a genuine balance community in northern virginia .
the problem , i surmise -- it 's not discuss in the story -- be that arlington be concern about protect its tax base , which mean replace the vacated office with new office , not house .
it 's hard to fault arlington for pursue its short - term self interest .
but everyone need to recognize that arlington 's decision not to pursue a balanced community mean that house will end up somewhere else , presumably in outlying county .
and employee work in the buff up crystal city will wind up commute long distance and clog northern virginia thoroughfare .
