michael jackson
manchild in a promise land
by robert j. lewis
he 's such an easy target , michael jackson .
he make even the weirdest of the weird feel normal .
but unlike them , jackson do n't try to hide the fact that he be easily one of the most screw up being on the planet .
every time he check in for yet another surgery , he be announce to the world that he do n't know who he be , where he be go , and that he thoroughly loathe himself - at least the adult version .
and for his remarkable honesty , his most unprivate confession , he be subject to one public humiliation after another .
who among us rock thrower would have the courage to reveal about ourselves what michael have reveal about himself ?
next to the tower monument that the unedited michael jackson be we be telephone booth ;
next to his singular guilelessness and candor , we be the multitude of the prevaricate and pusillanimous .
everything michael have do and say during the past 20 year have be against his own apparent self - interest , begin with unrelenting surgical assault on his erstwhile good look , to hang his child ( and crotch for that matter ) out to dry , to enter detail of his bedroom antics into the public domain .
like a typical dostoievksy character , we can not account for the behavior if it be n't for an apparently override need to confess and proclaim -- over and against what the outside world want to believe -- the truth of who we be .
the on - go spectacle of michael 's increasingly bizarre conduct be his confession to the world that he be one spectacularly psychologically - challenged dude .
like children who be incapable of dissimulate their basic want and need , michael 's manner of be in the world be uncensored and spontaneous ,
and to such an unsuspected extent i propose he deserve to be consider one of the most authentic being of this or any other century , and quite properly belong to that exceptional society of authenticity - questers that would include saint augustine , pascal and heidegger .
the fact of michael 's life have be well document .
we know that by the age of 25 he be on top of the world .
thriller have sell an unprecedented 50 million copy and billie jean have become the musical drug of choice in every corner of the world .
not only be the song 's momentum and tension brilliantly craft and fuse , michael 's rivet , counterpoint choreography - which remain unsurpassed -- revolutionized the way we simultaneously look at and listen to music .
before disbelieve eye , his torso , head and limb supply never - before - see anatomical rejoinder to the note -- like a guitarist fill in between the lyric .
but from here on in , it would be downhill for the genre 's quintessential messenger , for michael could no long sustain the ' great lie ' he be live .
the child 's ' tin drum ' be beat ever louder in his head
and he intuitively understand that he be developmentally under - equip to handle the adult pressure of stardom .
far more compel than the promise of even greater fame and fortune be the example of oskar , from gunther grass ' the tin drum ( 1959 ) , which tell the story of a boy who refuse to grow up , who , through his drum , reject the adult world and the horror take place in nazi germany .
like oskar , michael have witness firsthand the abomination of adult behaviour and refuse to sign up .
from his early year , michael jackson be subject to both extreme psychological and physical abuse at the hand of his status - obsess father , who designate michael as the vessel into which he would mercilessly pour the acid of his unrealized ambition .
to this single end , joe jackson be ruthlessly single - minded .
michael be terrify of him , whose mere presence could induce nausea .
at the age of 5 , the father yank the son from his pail and sandbox existence and make him run hollywood 's grimmest gauntlet .
the little mouse that michael be suddenly find himself in the rat race and quickly learn to hate it ,
and like oskar , who find respite in the beat of his tin drum , michael find solace on stage , perform his music .
but the stage could not provide michael with immunity against the constant encroachment of the adult world .
listen to his rapid breathe in especially off the wall and thriller : the staccato - like pant of a stalk animal , the desperate breath of human panic , and his small boy 's voice hide behind the mesmerize slash and blur of arm and leg fending off an invisible attack .
from one track to the next , the lyric be n't so much sung as frantically whisper , the vowel cut short to the quick .
michael be announce that he could no longer follow the course father and hollywood have stake out for him , that the disparity between his real self and the role he be thrust into have reach unsustainable incommensurability .
only the child within could save the defenceless adult from the depredation of the adult world ,
and from this point on , michael would reduce the project of his life to let the world know the truth of who he be : a confused , fragile , lose soul in search of care and love .
by the time michael have attain mythic status , he be so far remove and alienate from himself , he would have to shed , over a period of 20 year and still count , one skin after another before his true self could begin to emerge .
as we might expect from someone so radically self - estrange , the result have be nothing less than a metamorphosis .
michael 's journey of self - discovery be a work in progress like no other because it increasingly depends on the accommodation of two irreconcilables : the child and adult as one .
more reveal of itself than its favorite target , public opinion have not see fit to grant michael the inalienable right to his confused mental state and ' off the wall ' comportment .
if most people subscribe to the notion that black and white be not only skin colors but state of mind , why be we baffle or offend when michael , who be introduce to the white way of hollywood at the age of 5 , tell us that he be n't sure what his true color be ?
rob of his childhood , abuse by a psychotic father and then prematurely subject to the adult pressure of the entertainment world , why be we surprise to learn that michael do n't want to grow up , that he prefer the company and community of children , that he want to be protect and look after ?
every time the androgynous jackson go under the knife he be cry out that he do n't know if he be man or woman , child or adult , black or white .
as if we would have do otherwise in his situation ?
and to the never - end suspicion that michael be a child abuser , what crime have be commit when two experiment 11 - year - olds fool around sexually ?
if you believe that michael have the mentality of an 11 - year - old , ( and there have n't be much evidence to the contrary during the past 20 year ) he should not have have to defend himself against accusation of child molestation .
was it in defense of perversity or his incorrigible innocence that convince him that it be ok to reveal that he share his bed with children ?
more questionable , even criminal , than michael 's alleged fool around with other kid , be the parent who allow , even encourage their children to sleep over and perhaps share the same bed with someone whose sexual predilection have be suspect since 1991 .
on june 13 , 2005 , the court find michael not guilty of the charge bring against him .
however , those whose mind be decide on his guilt before the trial begin will not be change by the verdict , just as michael 's essential nature will not have change .
mahatma gandhi write that ' there be a higher court than court of justice and that be the court of conscience . '
only michael know if he be sexually attract to children , and beyond that , if he have ever act on those feeling .
and if we grant him the mental age of an 11 - year - old , who have nonetheless conventionally father two children , michael be then a child trap in an adult body .
which mean the crown act in his quest for authenticity await one final operation .
what do a man do when he feel , act and respond like a woman trap in a man 's body ?
he undergo sexual reassignment surgery and hormone therapy in order to become who ' she ' be .
there remain one final procedure that will totally liberate the child that michael be .
when michael find the courage to act on what his duty toward other children demand -- submit to voluntary neuter -- which will be tantamount to his final confession , the save grace and glory that be his neverland will become his forever land .
tennessee williams have say for all time , `` there 's not enough kindness in the world . ''
and i say this to you , michael jackson , may your tribe increase .
`` thank god i 'm an atheist : ''
the surrealistic cinema of luis bunuel --
by bryan m. papciak
`` the thought of death have be familiar to me for a long time , '' say director luis bunuel .
`` from the time that skeleton be carry through the street of calanda during the holy week procession , death have be an integral part of my life .
i 've never wish to forget or deny it ,
but there 's not much to say about it when you 're an atheist '' ( 255 ) .
so read an accurate testimonial to the personal and artistic sentiment of this odd and serious filmmaker .
like many of his contemporary surrealist , bunuel be a paradox who on one hand claim apathy towards ultimate end , be , and be , yet on the other hand load his impressive body of work with moribund imagery and strange idea about the god he so vociferously deny .
bunuel exhibit a radical , iconoclastic view of the world in which he find society decadent and antithetical to human liberation .
he have be call a realist , a surrealist , a marxist , an anarchist , a mystic , an anticleric , a freudian , a post @-@ freudian , a sadist , a moralist , a christian , and a poet - showman of the macabre .
his scenario range from the absurd to the tragic to the satiric to the erotic , profusely endue with the outrageous and the scandalous .
luis bunuel have long be recognize in european critical circle as a great and prolific filmmaker on a par with eisenstein , chaplin , and fellini .
however , only recently have his reputation in america begun to catch up .
over his fifty - year career he direct thirty - two feature film and work in spain , france , mexico , italy , and the unite state .
utilize sardonic humor and the imagery of surrealism , bunuel set out to undermine the value and institution people take for grant .
his aim be specific : through the surreal , visualize the impulse of the uncon - scious , he would , he say , `` shatter the optimism of the bourgeoisie world and force the reader ( or spectator ) to question the permanency of the prevail order '' ( mellen 3 ) .
luis bunuel be born february 22 , 1900 in calanda , a small town in the province of teruel , spain .
as a youth he receive a jesuit education , display exceptional talent in music , athletics , and the natural science .
he enjoy a comfortable upbringing in a reasonably wealthy , close - knit family .
his family come from liberal , semi @-@ intellectual , land - own bourgeoisie .
these detail be not irrelevant .
to comprehend bunuel 's work it be essential to understand that he be first a spaniard and secondly a product of spanish bourgeoisie .
virginia higgenbotham point out that `` blasphemy be only a form of think for any intelligent spaniard , '' and also that the `` art of his country be rich in eroticism and profoundly preoccupy with death '' ( 18 , 20 ) .
bunuel say : my infancy slip by in an almost medieval atmosphere ( like that of nearly all the spanish province ) between my native town and zaragova .
i feel it necessary to say here ( since it explain in part the trend of the modest work which i late accomplish ) that the two basic sentiment of my childhood which stay with me well into adolescence , be those of a profound eroticism , at first sublimate in a great religious faith , and a permanent consciousness of death .
it would take too long here to analyze the reason .
it suffice that i be not an exception among my compatriot , since this be a very spanish characteristic , and our art , exponent of the spanish spirit , be impregnate with these two sentiment .
the last civil war , peculiar and ferocious as no other expose them clearly .
come of age , bunuel express a strong urge to go to paris to study music but be send instead to madrid to study agricultural engineer .
after a few year , he switch his study to entomology , and , more importantly , begin form close friendship with a group of young artist who be to influence him strongly in the future .
these companion include the poet frederico garcia lorca and jose moreno villa and the painter salvador dali .
in the madrid residencia bunuel develop his interest in the art , theater , and act and gain his introduction to surrealism .
after graduate in 1925 with a degree in philosophy and letter , bunuel move to paris , join by a few member of his residencia coterie .
bunuel arrive in paris highly recommend by influential friend of his parent and be introduce into the best intellectual circle of the city .
he be soon hire as an assistant director to jean epstien , `` the only director of that bleak era of the french cinema to merit the title of an intellectual filmmaker '' ( aranda 32 ) .
while hone his skill work as an a.d. , bunuel also begin contribute article to various literary cinema periodical , most notably la gaceta hispanoamericana .
in 1929 he formally enter the paris surrealist group .
within this set he embark on his first film project as director , a collaboration with his residencia friend salvador dali , entitle un chien andalou .
he collaborate with dali again in 1930 on another surrealist film , l_age d ' or .
the rest , as they say , be history .
some critic , most notably pauline kael and penelope gilliatt , now regard bunuel as the hitchcock of surrealism -- a venerated master in total command of his medium and for whom the art of filmic manipulation become a `` delightful form of play . ''
for bunuel , however , play have little to do with it .
rather , he see surrealism as a revolutionary , poetic , and moral movement :
all of us be supporter of a certain concept of revolution , and although the surrealist do n't consider themselves terrorist , they be constantly fight a society they despise .
the principle weapon be not gun , of course , it be scandal .
scandal be a potent agent of revelation , capable of expose such social crime as exploitation of one man by another , colonialist imperialism , religious tyranny -- in sum , all the secret and odious underpinnings of a system that have to be destroy .
he go on to say , `` the purpose of surrealism be not to create a new literary , artistic , or even philosophical movement , but to explode the social order , to transform life itself ' ( 107 ) .
salvador dali recall the surrealist ' ideology , `` it be possible to systematize confusion thank to a paranoia and active process of thought and so assist in discredit completely the world of reality '' ( gould 37 ) .
indeed , the intent of surreal art be to move one from the conscious mind into the subconscious .
it seek to affect the emotion through the mind .
michael gould state in surrealism and the cinema , `` if the vision reveal be too much for the rational mind to absorb ( too intense , too threaten , too ' real ' ) yet can not be reject , then it leave the consciousness and come to exist on a sublime level as pure surrealism '' ( 13 ) .
in un chien andalou , for example , a girl 's eye be slice with a razor blade ,
a man wipe his mouth completely off his face ,
dead donkey carcass adorn a piano ,
a man 's hand crawl with ant .
each of these image be clearly too intense for rational thought .
bunuel be draw to the surrealist movement for more than revolutionary or psychological reason .
the moral aspect of the movement intrigue him as well :
for the first time in my life , i 'd come into contact with a coherent moral system that , as far as i could tell , have no flaw .
it be an aggressive morality based on the complete rejection of all exist value .
we have other criteria :
we exalt passion , mystification , black humor , the insult , and the call of the abyss .
inside this new territory , all our thought and action seem justifiable ;
there be simply no room for doubt .
everything make sense .
our morality may have be more demanding and more dangerous than the prevail order , but it be also stronger , richer , more coherent .
the surreal quality in bunuel 's film can be trace to a number of source ,
but the primary impetus be his `` irrational sensibility '' as evidence by his treatment of image , montage , and sound .
these give his film their dreamlike quality .
his most intense image be evocative of either humor or mystery .
mystery , he believe , be the essential element of any art ;
it be inseparable from chance ,
and the whole universe be a mystery ,
bunuel believe that his own form of atheism lead inevitably to the acceptance of the inexplicable .
`` since i reject the idea of a divine watchmaker , '' he say , `` ( a notion even more mysterious than the mystery it supposedly explain ) , then i must consent to live in a kind of shadowy confusion ....
at least it keep my moral freedom intact '' ( 174 ) .
predictably , adherence to fantasy as oppose to reason in a rationalistic society lead to conflict .
the surrealist oppose nearly all traditional value and , as note before , seek to destroy `` all conventional social , moral , and artistic habit of thought and perception '' ( higgenbotham 30 ) .
enter un chien andalou .
in 1929 , un chien andalou be as shock and scandalous as bunuel and dali have hope it would be .
it give rise to a stagger range of interpretation : poetic , scandalous , incoherent , an attack upon critic , an attack upon religion , and attack upon the bourgeoisie .
( interestingly , the film be finance by bunuel 's bourgeois mother . )
un chien andalou ( which mean an andalusian dog -- though there be no dog in the film ) be deliberately intend to jolt the spectator 's peace of mind and to convey some of the basic belief underlie the surrealist movement , include the omnipotence of desire .
bunuel state that he and dali hold to only one rule during the production ,
`` no idea or image that might lend itself to rational explanation of any kind would be accept .
we have to open all door to the irrational and keep only those image that surprise us without try to explain why '' ( 104 ) .
the aim of the film be not exclusively to shock , but to incendiarially affect the collective conscience .
at the same time it be an indictment of all the art consumer who , either through stupidity , masochism , or self interest , be willing to swallow anything , no matter how much it go against their instinct .
bunuel ask , `` what can i do about the people who adore all that be new , even when it go against their deep conviction , or about the insincere , corrupt press and the inane herd that see beauty and poetry in something which be basically no more than a desperate call for murder ? '' ( bauche 9 ) .
the film be a dream and , like a dream , be both fascinate and disturb .
the open scene in which a girl 's eye be slice set the tone of the film 's meander and confuse itinerary .
many of the element that make up the film be remnant of objective reality .
the way they be arrange within the scenario push them into a mental reconstruction process -- in exactly the way dream draw on the previous day 's experience .
interestingly , the image have the matter - of - fact quality of a newsreel , or what higgenbotham call a `` prosaic realism '' ( 38 ) .
bunuel choose not to use the distort lens , supered image , or blur focus ( cinematic convention of the day ) to suggest the dreamlike quality of his film .
instead , he approach the entire non @-@ narrative in a straightforward manner .
he use the shock incongruity of the image themselves to build the hallucinatory feel of anguish that run through the film .
the unrealistic fashion in which the realistic image be juxtapose be the perfect way , accord to freddy bauche , to illustrate `` the dramatic collision between desire and the object of desire '' ( 10 ) .
obviously , the director draw much of un chien andalou from his spanish heritage -- the religious and social implication , the theme of emotionalism and death , even the donkey carcass .
`` thus un chien andalou , as a milestone in the history of cinema , emerge from its director 's adolescence in spain and announce the theme and technique that be to preoccupy bunuel for half a century , through the rest of his career '' ( higgenbotham 39 ) .
where desire and eroticism prevail in un chien andalou , religion take center stage in simon del desierto ( simon of the desert ) , produce in mexico in 1965 .
simon del desierto be a bizarre little narrative set in the fifth century a.d.
saint simon , in order to be as close to god as possible , have stand pray on top of a sixty - foot pillar for thirty - seven year .
he be profoundly sanctimonious - to the degree that he even bless his own tooth when it fall from his mouth .
his devotion , however , be put to the test when the devil ( a woman wear the uniform of a catholic school girl ) arrive in a slither coffin at the pillar .
she be intent on lure the holy disciple from his perch as she repeatedly ridicule him and insult his character .
simon heroically resist her temptation at every turn despite her various disguise ; first , a priest , then a shepherd , and finally as the savior himself .
at last , despite simon 's holy strength , and for reason not entirely clear , the devil be able to exert her full power and whisk him away to hell -- a greenwich village disco where trendy writhe and grind to `` the radioactive flesh . ''
the implication be stagger .
`` the saint , devoted to his god , sit high on a pillar for all of life ....
but the pillar , discolored over the year , wind and twist its way to the ground , be the excrement of the saint .
saint though he be , his bowel must still move .
so there he sit , near god indeed , but support on a pillar of excrement '' ( mellen 115 ) .
there have be several interpretation of this seemingly blasphemous imagery .
one be that god and his church be really build on unacknowledged humanity .
another be that we can reach god only through understand the true nature of our humanity .
still another be that religion ( primarily catholicism ) be essentially a `` pillar of excrement . ''
bunuel himself put all the interpretation in perspective when he say , `` thank god i 'm still an atheist . ''
luis bunuel 's flair for perverse surrealism and his malicious attack on conventional morality be fully realize in his second to last film , le fantome de la liberte ( the phantom of liberty ) , produce in france in 1974 -- almost fifty year after un chien andalou .
fantome in many way function as a sort of sequel to his 1972 film , le channe discret de la bourgeoisie ( the discreet charm of the bourgeoisie ) .
the image be astound and playfully absurd :
spanish hostage of the napoleonic war cry `` down with freedom ! '' as they be execute .
a french lieutenant fondle the statue of a beautiful noblewoman and be struck on the head by another statue .
bourgeois couple discuss defecation around a toilet - line table but consider `` food '' an impolite topic , and so on .
the titular reference to a `` phantom '' boffows from the open line of karl marx 's communist manifesto :
`` a specter be haunt europe - the specter of communism . ''
bunuel twist this mean to imply that the specter haunt the bourgeoisie be `` the possibility of its own freedom unburden by the dead end of sexual license , willful irrationality , and the liberty to go beyond the self - indulgent eccentricity of the individual ego '' ( mellen 318 ) .
bunuel compare the film to one of his earlier surrealist work , l_age d ' or , say , `` it be no long possible to scandal @-@ ize people as we do in 1930 .
today you have to do it with sweet subversion '' ( mellen 183 ) .
le fantome de la liberte charge that society have substitute arbitrary willfulness for freedom .
one of the film 's vignette show two parent who insist on declare their daughter a miss person , although she be plainly sit in front of them .
the police , in a similar display of willful blindness to reality , even ask the child herself for her vital statistic and how she disappear .
in another episode , four chain - smoke monk gamble with their holy medallion in a card game .
`` i 'll open with a virgin , '' say one .
another play a `` father . ''
bunuel believe reality be actually a smoke screen for hidden urge .
he use the absurd to imply `` an attack on specific abuse , not on some safely vague condition of man '' ( durgnat 65 ) .
in le fantome de la liberte bunuel doubt not so much the possibility for society 's redemption as its likelihood .
`` we have be render unwittingly comfortable within our psychic cage to the point where we prefer them to liberty , an experience and aspiration we neither understand or desire '' ( mellen 331 ) .
for fifty year , luis bunuel make film about society 's dilemma .
his art be his declaration of confidence in a human race dominate by a bourgeoisie give to hypocrisy , sadism , and above all , a disrespect for its own capacity to live differently and better .
he summed it all up himself :
as i drift toward my last sigh , i often imagine a final joke .
i convoke around my deathbed my friend who be confirm atheist as i be .
then a priest , whom i have summon , arrive ;
and to the horror of my friend , i make my confession , ask for absolution for my sin , and receive extreme unction .
after which i turn over on my side and expire .
but will i have the strength to joke at that moment ?
luis bunuel die in 1983 .
