anyway , here 's a short piece from mother jones :
thrown to the assassin
they cheer the u.s. invasion ;
they offer to help , sign on as translator , risk everything they have to work for the unite state .
but when they have to run for their life , america slam the door .
by david case / mother jones
on the day the american tank roll into baghdad , abather abdul hussein and his wife , balqes abdel mohammed , throw flower .
literally .
after a lifetime of turmoil and tyranny , the couple fervently believe the invasion would bring peace .
abather join u.s. `` democratization '' effort , such as a project to create a govern council for his neighborhood , and he occasionally end up in the good - news iraq story that still seem plausible in those day ;
one u.s. paper run a five - column photo of him perch on a classroom chair surround by american soldier , with a story about the `` new iraq . ''
these day , abather and his young family be among the hundred of thousand of iraqis who have flee in fear for their life .
after month spend dodge insurgent who have targeted them for support the americans , he and balqes be relieve to have escape -- and bitter , like thousand of fellow refugee , that the superpower for which they risk their life have abandon them .
a short man who bundle his shatter body in layer against the desert 's winter chill , the 34 - year - old abather be polite and relax , with an easy smile .
an engaging conversationalist even in break english , he love to talk about baghdad , his infant daughter , and his wife , an outspoken woman several year his senior , whom he call a genius .
`` when we meet she be a professor at baghdad university , '' he boast .
`` i be her student .
when she walk into a room , hundred of people would stand to pay her respect . ''
consider that his life savings will run out in two month , that he can n't work legally in jordan , and that he could be deport at any moment , abather be remarkably stoic , though the anxiety leak out in tic .
he chain - smoke cheap craven a cigarette , crush the charred filter in an overflow ashtray ;
when balqes complain , he sheepishly offer that `` smoke be my only work . ''
it 's not quite true --
his one other job during the past 18 month have be recount his nightmare , over and over again , to border guard , embassy worker , and aid agency .
in december , he reluctantly tell it to me , pull document from a worn leather folder to corroborate the detail .
the story begin after the ouster of saddam , when abather and balqes , like many iraqis , launch a de @-@ baathification program of their own .
their target be the dean who have be balqes ' boss at baghdad university ( and who , as abather tell it , have force her out when she resist join the baath party ) .
balqes want her job back ;
one day abather confront the dean ,
and temper flare .
american soldier break up the brawl , bound abather 's wrist with a zip tie , and interrogate him .
he explain balqes ' gripe and what the loss of her job have mean for their family , include their 3 - year - old son and balqes ' 14 - year - old son from a previous marriage ( her first husband have be kill in the iran - iraq war ) .
though he hold a master 's degree in engineer , abather have n't be able to get a job in the doldrums of sanction - era iraq ,
so he be scrape together a live repair watch , his wife and children cram into his father 's small home .
`` the soldier be very understand , '' abather recall .
`` i be impress . ''
they offer the family an apartment in a place call iraqi village , a compound near the baghdad airport where saddam have house orphan he be groom to become fedayeen loyalist .
in return , the couple translate for the americans , and eventually the washington national guard 's 1 st battalion 303 rd armored regiment hire balqes as an interpreter , at $ 15 per day .
abather end up lead a u.s. army - contract security squad with a monthly salary of $ 130 .
learn that he be an engineer , soldier later gave him lucrative reconstruction assignment .
he start an engineer firm and work with contractor such as abb and kellogg , brown and root ;
in one heady year , abather 's contract would mushroom from a few thousand dollar to an $ 862,000 electrification project ( later canceled because he could n't procure the need equipment ) .
abather and balqes glow with wonder when they speak of those day , of earn a good live and have their own home for the first time .
most of all , abather enjoy hang out with the americans .
he seem to remember every soldier he ever meet :
captain philips and sergeant buchard give his children toy , a soccer ball , and school stationery ;
lieutenant glenn allen get so close to the family they call him `` uncle allen . ''
( allen confirm abather 's story in emails to me , call him and balqes `` very helpful individual '' who `` risk their life by meet with us . '' )
it be as if they have suddenly find themselves citizen of the 51 st state .
and so , in october 2004 , when abather get his first death threat , he think it be a joke .
it be handwritten , tuck under the windshield wiper of his car inside iraqi village , a gate community with american checkpoint at both its entrance ;
the note read :
abather , leave your work with the americans .
otherwise you will be kill by jihadis because you be a traitor .
jihad army
then the killings begin .
lieutenant allen have once give abather a photo depict two american soldier with five of their iraqi friend .
three of the iraqis be assassinate in short order .
abather begin to notice car follow him ,
and a few time shot be fire at his car .
the anonymous note grow increasingly menace .
eventually , iraqi village feel so dangerous that abather and balqes move the family back to his father 's house .
a death threat arrive there almost immediately .
still abather continue work with the americans .
one day in august 2005 , abather be drive balqes , six month pregnant with their second child , to a doctor 's appointment .
at an intersection , he notice a gold car park by the road ;
suddenly the two men in it leveled gun at him .
`` this be the end , '' abather think ,
and then a u.s. patrol appear
and the assailant vanish into traffic .
within day , abather and balqes have sell off their belongings and flee to amman .
their trouble have only just begin .
the u.s. embassy in amman be an attractive , arabian - style fortress , heavily guard machine - gunner in ford pickups .
it sit high on a hillside ,
and the view be so phenomenal that you can imagine your gaze reach all the way to the iraqi border , some 200 mile away .
in the foreground , amman 's roll mosaic of pale , boxy limestone building shimmer against the azure sky .
at its edge , in dank apartment on outlying hillside , life a substantial portion of baghdad 's educate middle class .
almost all flee in a panic , after get death threat or see love one murder ;
many be targeted by insurgent or jihadis because they support , or work for , the americans .
of iraq 's 27 million prewar population , about 1 in 8 -- some 3.4 million people -- have leave their home since the invasion , accord to the unite nation high commission for refugee ( unhcr ) ,
and more than half of those have end up abroad .
refugee international label this the world 's fast - grow humanitarian crisis .
yet the bush administration have refuse to so much as acknowledge the refugee ' plight , let alone help them get to safety or even provide basic humanitarian aid .
in the past , note bill frelick , refugee policy director at human right watch , the unite state have often aid those persecute for support it ;
since the vietnam war , 1 million vietnamese refugee have be resettle in the unite state , include ten of thousand of south vietnamese army veteran .
but the bush administration `` have abdicate that obligation , '' say frelick .
`` the people who have flee be the one the administration be relying on to build democracy in iraq ;
it would rather ignore them than acknowledge that its initiative have fail . ''
it be in jordan that abather and balqes discover the limitation of their friendship with the unite state .
lieutenant `` uncle '' allen have emailed the embassy in amman to explain that the family fear for their life ;
he 'd even offer to sponsor their relocation `` to the safety of the unite state . ''
an unsigned email from the embassy commend allen -- '' i know that your iraqi friend appreciate your friendship '' -- but note that u.s. visa be `` quite difficult '' for iraqis to get .
since 9 / 11 , middle easterners in general , and iraqis in particular , have face enormous hurdle get admit to the unite state ;
until 2005 , the bush administration maintain a total freeze on iraqis that shut out current refugee as well as hundred of people who have flee saddam hussein 's regime year earlier .
the email nonetheless provide instruction on get a tourist visa ,
and abather and balqes quickly file their application along with the $ 200 fee -- almost two month ' rent .
several month later they be notify that they could visit the unite state for up to three month , but that they could not bring their children .
they then make repeat visit to the unhcr to apply for official refugee status .
as it have with almost 99 percent of the iraqis who have come through its office in amman , the agency turn them down .
abather and balqes set their sight on a visa to australia , a major destination for iraqi refugee , and even hire an iraqi lawyer there .
they wait for month .
their savings dwindle ;
then their baby fall ill ,
and the emergency surgery , for an intestinal obstruction , cost $ 2,100 in cash .
in early june 2006 , abather get a rejection letter from australia .
around the same time , word come that his father have die of a heart attack .
so he go back to iraq to bury his father , help his mother find a place to live , and buy state - subsidize medicine for his daughter .
but when he return to the jordanian border less than a week later , he be tell he could n't reenter the country :
have recently suffer two terrorist attack , jordan have enact a ban on entry for iraqi men age 17 to 35 .
for two day abather stand on the highway at the border post , beseech successive shift of immigration official .
finally , a guard promise to send the medicine to his family in amman if he would just go away .
once again abather head back to baghdad .
drive in baghdad a few day later , he notice a bmw -- the iraqi gangster 's vehicle of choice -- in his rearview mirror , closing in .
the car force him off the road ;
arm man blindfold him and knock him unconscious .
when he wake up , he be in a tiny room , handcuff to a chair .
mask men come and go , videotape as they curse him as a traitor .
they whip him with a steel cable ;
six month later , his back be still etch by deep , evenly space groove .
`` we 've be search for you for a year , '' his captor tell him .
abather recognize the voice of one man , an acquaintance from iraqi village who have seem to befriend the americans .
`` i 'm sorry your father pass away , '' the man say .
soon , a bearded imam sentence abather to decapitation for collaborate with the unite state .
abather barely hear the proceeding .
`` i be think the whole time about my little daughter in amman . ''
he be tell he could save himself by spy on the americans , but he refuse .
on the eighth day , the men ask if there be anything he want before he die ;
then they put him on the floor in the back of the bmw and speed off .
suddenly , abather hear gunshot .
the men shout .
the car crash ,
and everything go black .
he wake up in a hospital bed 60 mile from baghdad ;
iraqi force have attack the bmw and pull him from the burn wreck .
he have a compound fracture in his leg and severe burn all over his body ,
but the nurse urge him to leave :
his captor would be look for him .
his brother -- who have receive a ransom note from the kidnapper , complete with a photo of abather bound and gag -- brought him back to baghdad , where doctor fuse a piece of plastic onto his shin and graft skin from his thigh over his wound .
a few week later , he be back at the jordanian border ,
and this time the guard take pity .
the family have n't tell balqes of the kidnap .
but when she see her disfigure husband , she say , `` i know right away what happen . ''
on a crisp , clear day this past december , clutch a sheaf of paper document abather and balqes ' ordeal -- contract , soldier ' recommendation , death threat , a miss - person report -- i head to american citizen service at the u.s. embassy in amman .
abather and balqes have make several pilgrimage there ;
they be convince that if only they could speak to an american , abather 's char and mangle flesh would make their case , but they have never get past the jordanian security guard .
outside the embassy , i join a chatty , eclectic crowd of americans : a retire hippie turn english teacher from vermont ; a woman with a new york accent who struggle through the narrow eye - slit in her black veil to keep track of her hyperactive daughter ; a white - bearded man in a santa hat , who say he be pick up his passport before return to the north pole .
i wonder whether any of us would risk our life for the unite state as abather and balqes have .
to get past the compound 's first wall , we navigate a metal detector , a body frisk , and an x @-@ ray machine ;
after cross a 30 - foot no man 's land we repeat the process at the second wall .
then we wait to be call .
the unite state admit more refugee than any country in the world ,
but in 2006 , only 202 iraqis be allow in ,
and most of them have flee persecution under saddam before the war .
this year , million of iraqis , tibetans , sri lankans , and afghans must compete for a mere 5,500 refugee slot congress have allocate for the middle east and south asia .
the iraqis be in line behind their compatriot who have be wait in jordan since the late 1990 s .
like other western representative , u.s. official here refer displace people to the unhcr , which be charge with determine whether someone be a real refugee , and if so , with find him a safe place to go .
except that , as amman unhcr head robert breen tell me , a 1998 agreement with jordan forbid the agency from classify anyone as a refugee whom it can n't get out of the country within six month -- an impossibility in the post / 11 world .
( a country of about 6 million , jordan have long have the world 's highest refugee population per capita , host more than a million palestinians who flee israel in 1948 and be suppose to stay only a short time . )
of the 21,000 iraqi asylum seeker the office have register since the u.s. invasion , only 291 have be grant refugee status ; meanwhile the line outside the unhcr 's gate get longer every week ,
and the wait for an interview stand at five month .
to care for all of the region 's displace iraqis , the agency have a total budget of $ 22 million in 2006 -- less than $ 7 a person , which must cover not only the kafkaesque registration programs but also basic survival aid to refugee trap in desert camp or squat in abandoned building .
recognize the potential for `` severe humanitarian suffer , '' the iraq study group in december recommend that `` the unite state take the lead '' in fund the unhcr 's iraq program ;
currently it donate no more than a quarter of the budget .
direct u.s. aid to the refugee consists of a tiny grant to the catholic relief organization caritas ( see `` how to help , '' page 68 ) .
at the embassy , i recount abather and balqes ' ordeal at window 3 , then at window 1 -- the setup be similar to visitation in a high - security prison .
then , at window 4 , i tell the story again to the consul general , who stood behind the bulletproof glass wear a telephone headset .
i be expect to hear that `` the unite state be do its best to help , ''
but there be only silence as the consul 's eye well up .
( an amman - based aid worker later told me that american diplomat be so distraught by the policy they be charge with represent that `` it just take a few gin and tonic and they 'll break down . '' )
finally , the consul say , `` we hear story like this all the time .
we have enormous empathy for the iraqis who 've suffer after work with the americans ,
but there 's really nothing the embassy can do for them . ''
she hand me a document outline congress ' sole concession to people like abather and balqes : visa for up to 50 military translator from iraq or afghanistan each year .
`` but do n't get their hope up , '' she add quickly ;
there be thousand with the same story .
`` this be something congress really need to address , '' she say as we part .
the administration certainly do n't seem incline to take the initiative .
philip a. frayne , an embassy spokesman in amman , tell me that `` there be no reliable figure '' on how many people have flee iraq , and that in any case , it be saddam who drive out `` a large percentage '' of them .
likewise , in its 2006 annual refugee report to congress , the state department focused mainly on those saddam - era exile , and blithely intone , `` it be hope that significant number of iraqi refugee will soon be able to return home , although the security situation will remain an important consideration . ''
the report ignore the fact that , accord to a survey by the nonprofit u.s. committee for refugee , 644,500 new refugee enter jordan and syria in 2005 alone .
and 2006 will likely be worse .
as much as a quarter of greater amman 's population be now iraqi ,
and the crowd have exacerbate the city 's severe water shortage .
price have skyrocket .
until recently iraqi children could n't attend jordanian school ,
and their parent can not legally work ;
easily identify by their dialect , iraqis be discriminate against and terrify of deportation .
some refugee never go outside .
jordanian government spokesman nasser s. judeh tell me that his country , a staunch u.s. ally and aid recipient , `` certainly need help , and have hold discussion with u.s. diplomat '' about this issue .
incidentally , human right watch have also call upon the gulf arab state to pitch in ;
saudi arabia 's response so far have be to plan construction of a 560 - mile wall along its border with iraq .
before i leave jordan , abather invite me to visit his family and a physician friend from baghdad who share their two - room basement apartment .
on the al zawraa tv channel from baghdad , we watch u.s. army vehicle disappear behind roadside bomb blast as a man sang , `` let 's go kill the americans ! ''
the channel 's endless stream of anti @-@ american propaganda perplex abather and his friend :
`` why do the unite state allow this ? '' they inquire .
when image of dead children supposedly kill by the americans hit the screen , abather 's friend switch to a channel on which voluptuous arab women dance in an un @-@ islamic way .
balqes serve iraqi coffee ,
and to keep the baby from play with the colorful cup , abather suspend her from an elastic swing above our head .
she giggle as he bounce her by her tiny foot .
this be her prison , he joke .
six month after the kidnap , he still have n't get the surgery he need to heal his burn flesh ;
if the wound become infect , he could die .
abather rarely complain .
god be test us , he say .
but we will get through it .
he look at the girl bounce from the ceiling and smile .
i have a daughter ,
and i 'm very happy .
balqes be more fearful -- twice in the past month , suspicious men have show up at the apartment .
iraq , she worry , have already catch up with them .
how to help
very few organization be work on get aid to iraqi refugee , and of those that be , many be too small or too beleaguer to accept individual donation ;
the iraqi red crescent , for example , have suffer bombings and mass kidnappings , yet its volunteer continue to deliver aid to displace family inside iraq .
one of the larger relief organization work with the refugee be the catholic group caritas , whose caseworker i shadow while in amman .
buck the image of the land rover - drive aid worker , they make their round in an aging gray honda , its roof eat through by rust .
they visit iraqi doctor , engineer , and executive desperate for food , heat , or blanket to fend off the desert winter ;
one family tell the crew they have just sell their stove to buy food .
caritas help a few thousand family a year ,
but the demand far outstrip the money available to us , say magy mahrous , who oversee the project .
you can make a contribution at : international catholic migration commission citibank usa 153 east 53 rd street , 16 th floor new york , ny 10043 account # 10100491 , aba # 21000089 , swift code citius33
to ensure that the money reach the iraqi program , write iraq - icmc on your check .
at first , i sign up for a blog on donews , think that it be a site for it professional where i could perhaps find friend more easily .
later , i sign up for another one on msn , feel that write on msn might make it easier for me to communicate directly with my msn pal .
but gradually , i discover that both site be not very good .
at that time , donews do not have the function of tally traffic statistic ( i have the habit of look at the statistic of everything ) ; and even though msn have that function , others need to sign on to msn before they could reply , this meant that after read the entry , many could not reply even if they want to , hence largely reduce the interactive element .
the enthusiasm with write the blog at the begin be short - lived ; after write a few original article for promotion , i do not continue anymore .
at that time , i do n't think about post article from other site as i feel that there be no need to post any article if i could not come up with anything original ; this meant that sometimes for over two month i do n't even update a new entry .
later , there be also some minor problem with both msn and donews , so i become more unwilling to post new article .
so , these two blogs have not really be very popular , either
one of the hypotheses state : a long time ago , in order to hide from wild beast roam on the land , human have ever live in shallow water region for a long period of time , survive on aquatic plant and fish .
therefore , the body hair , which increase the friction in water , have fall off .
the reason for this explanation be that the fine hair on the back of human run from one side of the shoulder toward the spine , a different direction from that of monkey .
only such a direction could reduce the friction in water , and provide more buoyancy for the person who be swim in the water .
however , in all the primitive gather settlement that have be discover so far , we have not see any settlement where people live in such a way .
what be worse be -- from the perspective of the direction of the fine hair as well -- the fine hair on human ' upper arm point downward , while the fine hair on the lower arm point upward , which be to say , they all run toward the elbow .
this be somewhat similar to monkey who have hair : when it rain , they would hold their head with their hand , and such a direction of their hair would be easier for the rain to flow away along their elbow
what be saddam prosecute for ?
earlier on , iran 's involvement with the euro - for - oil transaction turn out to be a big news item with negligible after - effect , and finally it become a non @-@ issue , and hence there be no problem for iran and the unite state .
but this time , putin come up with a ruble - for - oil proposal , and even begin intensive preparation .
nobody would have any doubt about the technical capacity of russia , not to mention its ability to protect its own resource and trade system ,
the intimidation that russia have inflicted on ukraine be still remember with a tinge of fear by some european brother - like country .
the ruble be allow to float freely now , but everyone still have sufficient reason to doubt the replacement of the us dollar in dollar - for - oil .
but what be more vicious about comrade putin be that he have roll out what be know as a " barbarous " gold system ; and that be , before the wide acceptance of the ruble - for - oil , a portion of russia 's annual oil revenue would be channeled toward increase the country 's holding of gold .
this be the first among all major country to have issue such a clear proclamation - no wonder the recent link between gold and oil have almost be sever .
follow the government 's announcement of new immigration regulation , all travelers arrive in new zealand will receive the same treatment as they would receive when go to the us .
when they enter the country , they will be ask to provide biometric information .
at a press conference this afternoon , new immigration law confirm by immigration minister david cunliffe will give immigration official the power to collect , store and use biometric information of non @-@ new zealand citizen .
these so - call non @-@ new zealand citizen include people with a tourist , temporary or residency visa .
these new regulation be very similar to procedure for enter the us .
the new immigration law also permit the immigration service to provide " limited " biometric information on new zealand citizen to neighboring country .
however , the law do not explain the reason .
cunliffe say , it have presently not be decide when or how the biometric information will be collect from people 's body .
the government have introduce legislation that will permit further collection of dna sample from people 's body .
the new regulation on biometric information be only one article among the sixty - one article that make up the new regulation .
cunliffe say the new regulation will effectively simplify border - entry procedure and protect citizen ' right and international human right .
in new westminster , a homicide occur yesterday in an apartment where many chinese reside ,
a youth in his 20 s be suspect to have be seriously attack after he leave a party ; he be find lie in one of the apartment unit , and be pronounce dead upon arrival at the hospital .
after the event , two men be detain by the police to assist in the investigation , the motive of the murder remain unclear , and the case be now referred to the provincial integrate homicide investigation team for further investigation .
accord to the spokesman for the provincial integrate homicide investigation team , dale carr , the crime scene be in an apartment unit on the 800 block of agnes street ( agnes st. ) in new westminster .
the police receive an emergency 911 call at 12 @:@ 20 a.m . yesterday , and rush to the address mention above to investigate .
when the police arrive at the scene , they find an injure man lie in the unit ; he be seriously wound , and certify dead upon arrival at the hospital .
the body be send to the coroner for an autopsy in order to determine the cause of death .
for now , the police will not announce the name of the victim ; it will be decide upon only after the family be notify .
as to the cause of the victim 's death , and whether the case be link to any illegal activity and others and etc. , the police decline comment .
carr also say that the police have apply for a search warrant from the court yesterday morning , and enter the unit in the afternoon with the warrant for a detailed investigation , in order to understand more about the incident .
investigator from the identification bureau also go to collect information from the scene later ,
as to the motive of the attack , and whether the police have find the weapon , the police have decline disclosure .
in the face of criticism and nitpick , i believe that jesus be weaker than darwin .
why ?
because darwin be allow to make mistake , since he be a human be ; but jesus be not allow to make mistake , since he have be describe as god .
darwin propose evolution theory , but it be just a theory , and he himself also admit that there be many question ,
others may agree with him , or they may accept some part while disagree with other part , or in the future we might discover that the general direction of darwin 's evolution be largely correct though fill with a lot of error , and that there might be an improve version of evolution which be more accurate and comprehensive than what darwin have propose .
but as the originator , darwin deserve much credit .
jesus be god , and the bible be the word of god .
god create everything , understand everything , predict the future , and be infinitely resourceful , so how can he be wrong !
therefore , if you find a sentence that be allegedly say by god , but effectively turn out to be wrong , then this god will be overthrow .
therefore , jesus be more vulnerable to criticism than darwin , because once an error be find , then he could not be the true god .
after the collapse of saddam hussein 's dictatorial regime , iraqi religious force have enter a period of revitalization and expansion ,
although the distribution system of the new legislative power in iraq have generally take care of the interest of all party , and find a relatively reasonable balance point among all ethnic group and sect -- otherwise a management committee , the interim constitution , and the current interim government would not have be successfully generate -- this do not mean that there be no contradiction among them .
from an internal point of view , shiites and kurds tend to see eye to eye on the political and economic benefit , and iraqi politics have almost become the arena of these two faction ,
although under the balance of interest some of sunni political figure be involve in politics , what the sunni radical group be most concern about be that the shiites would turn around and suppress them in the future .
in february of this year , a radical sunni organization attack the ali mosque , which be the religious shrine of shiite muslims , and this lead to the eruption of the conflict between iraq 's two largest party .
the assassination of the lebanese minister of industry have trigger off angry protest from supporter , plunge lebanon into yet another precarious situation .
in merely two short year , this minister be the fifth senior official to be assassinate ; this show that even after the force withdrawal of israeli troop , long - suffer lebanon still have n't usher in the peace that it hope for yet .
the unite state claim that the syrian government be the murderer , but syria retort by say that the accusation be " totally without foundation , and in disregard of fact . "
at this moment , the real murderer be probably titter , but the world have clearly see that any one of the regime of lebanese and iraqi be more fragile than the other .
the western media say that in the " post @-@ bush " garbage era , country like iraq , syria , and lebanon will encounter a lot more good show or terrible tragedy .
and the people believe that .
it be uncertain whether the canadian prime minister have take the political equivalent of viagra , or have lose his mind due to political bias , but he " lose his temper " several time in china during apec , and almost mess up his meet with president hu .
fortunately president hu be magnanimous enough not to take it to heart , and give him the honor of a 15 - minute meet .
however , when this fellow return to his own country , he boast recklessly by say that his meet with president hu have " important historical significance , " and even exaggerate by claim it as his " major diplomatic achievement . "
but those canadian opponent already disgruntle with him , see through his trick , could immediately tell that the meeting that president hu have such as with bush , abe , and putin all last over an hour ; a mere 15 - minute meet with you -- exclude the pleasantry and translation -- be no different from an extended hand - shake .
this early morning the soccer match between the chinese women 's team and the korean team have indeed make me excite , i be surprise by the match 's brilliance , and i also gain a new understand of the korean team .
they attack swiftly and fearlessly and coordinated with tacit understand , but look back at the chinese women 's soccer team , it be in an inferior position either in time - control or coordination .
we lose this game with no complaint .
but look at the match between the chinese men 's soccer team and the iranians , that goal -- the insult , provocative , and perverse goal -- make me question the quality of the iranian team and even of the people in that country .
the chinese team show their gut during this game ; they manifest the courage and fight spirit of chinese people .
we do not shy away from the powerful iranian team , but do our best ; it be n't until after an overtime and two round of penalty kick that we then regretfully lose the match .
let us remember the iranian team , remember this iranian player who score this goal -- borhani .
the ioc warrior return to our motherland with hope .
i believe there will eventually be a day when we will -- avenge
[] a high school teacher teach chemistry in the unite kingdom have appeal to the department of education to allow the view and theory that god create everything and intellectual life create the world to be introduce into school to be teach to student together along with darwin 's theory of evolution , which have be dominate the scientific community since the 19 th century , and let student judge between right and wrong for themselves .
[] the long - stand policy of british department of education have be that the theory such as god 's creation be " unsuitable " for primary and secondary education .
[] critic have point out that some scholar from non @-@ english country actually have long mistranslate evolution theory and misinterpret darwin 's original intent , and the translation itself have a natural development from low to high level , a falsehood with almost religious bearing .
[] also some western scholar - such as paleontologist and archaeologist from the unite kingdom , france , and germany in the 19 th and 20 th century - have long make use of the distorted theory of evolution and social darwinism derived from the argument to attempt to prove their point that certain race be more advanced than others .
